02:08.059 --> 02:10.538
There's tons of mountains
and tunnels, and I...

02:10.616 --> 02:11.785
Yeah...

02:17.410 --> 02:22.150
Did you read this article about Google
and users' private information? It's...

02:22.396 --> 02:24.539
disgraceful.
They're too powerful.

02:24.592 --> 02:25.606
Thanks.

02:25.639 --> 02:27.572
So, I have no service in here
because of all the tunnels.

02:27.619 --> 02:28.979
But, I did reach Gwen.

02:29.026 --> 02:31.662
She said that she's gonna take
the "X-Men" thing off IMDB.

02:31.716 --> 02:32.985
I did one.
That was enough.

02:33.025 --> 02:35.149
Nor am I playing Nemesis again.

02:35.536 --> 02:37.712
Well, they have to do it now
because uh...

02:37.755 --> 02:39.272
everyone's blogging about it already.

02:39.298 --> 02:43.065
Yeah, I'm sick of acting hanging
from wires in front of green screens.

02:43.132 --> 02:44.735
I've outgrown it.

02:45.168 --> 02:47.115
Fans are gonna be devastated.

02:47.188 --> 02:49.488
Oh, did you speak to um...

02:49.704 --> 02:50.761
What's his name?
Uh...

02:50.794 --> 02:52.551
- Urs.
- Urs, Urs Cobler?

02:52.584 --> 02:54.234
- Yeah.
- Is the genda set for tonight?

02:54.259 --> 02:55.302
Yeah, you're all set.

02:55.327 --> 02:56.780
You have just the three interviews.

02:56.807 --> 02:58.617
And then this presentation
of the award,

02:58.657 --> 03:00.017
and the official dinner.

03:00.164 --> 03:01.740
He's gonna meet us
at the train station

03:01.777 --> 03:04.960
and starts to take us
to the Dolder... der... Dolder.

03:05.857 --> 03:07.717
That, that's where
you want to stay, right?

03:07.774 --> 03:09.877
I've written the first draft.
Wanna hear it?

03:09.917 --> 03:10.991
Sure.

03:15.335 --> 03:17.818
"I'm very honored that
Wilhelm Melchior asked me

03:17.858 --> 03:20.758
to accept the prize
you're awading him tonight.

03:21.105 --> 03:23.359
As you all know,
he decided a long ago

03:23.396 --> 03:25.439
to stay away from
all public events.

03:25.552 --> 03:29.326
Not because he's shy or proud,
he's a modest and generous man.

03:29.401 --> 03:33.401
But, he insists on protecting
the peace and quiet he needs to write.

03:33.671 --> 03:35.521
I wish that I could
promise you all that

03:35.554 --> 03:38.541
I, myself, would place
this prize in hands.

03:39.021 --> 03:41.107
But, Wilhelm has forbidden me to do so.

03:41.151 --> 03:44.061
He asked me to join him,
tomorrow in Sils Maria,

03:44.121 --> 03:45.921
where he lives for part of the year,

03:45.948 --> 03:49.341
but on one condition:
That I come empty-handed.

03:51.521 --> 03:54.617
If I'm here tonight,
it's because I owe everything to him.

03:54.730 --> 03:57.551
He chose an unknown
18 year old actress

03:57.577 --> 04:00.353
for the lead in the play
you've all known: Maloja Snake,

04:00.406 --> 04:01.940
and then for the film.

04:01.996 --> 04:05.013
That unknown actress
who played Sigrid was me.

04:05.310 --> 04:08.376
In two months of shooting,
he gave me everything

04:08.410 --> 04:11.822
I needed to build...
build a career on: My career.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.387
Up to here,

04:13.453 --> 04:17.272
it's fine and then it's all
downhill to fragments.

04:18.281 --> 04:19.708
You want me to finish it for you?

04:19.755 --> 04:22.335
No, I am the one who has
to pay tribute to him.

04:22.393 --> 04:23.845
I have to find my own words.

04:23.871 --> 04:25.695
If I'm stuck,
I'll ask you, okay?

04:29.448 --> 04:30.708
So, Mappy says it's gonna take

04:30.734 --> 04:33.692
about two and a half hours
to get to Sils Maria from Zurich.

04:33.731 --> 04:35.254
We have a driver.

04:35.341 --> 04:36.391
Um...

04:36.603 --> 04:38.495
Also, I texted Wilhelm's wife.

04:38.941 --> 04:40.687
She hasn't gotten back to me yet.

04:40.993 --> 04:42.727
That's not like Rosa.

04:42.792 --> 04:44.867
You sure I use,
is it the right number?

04:46.231 --> 04:47.335
- CREEP'S LAWYER
- Urgh!

04:47.361 --> 04:49.383
Perhaps, I should take this.

04:50.469 --> 04:52.706
Good evening, dear master.

04:56.588 --> 04:59.462
I told your client,
my future ex-husband.

04:59.501 --> 05:01.731
I can not come to the meeting,

05:01.764 --> 05:06.011
quite simply because I'm abroad.

05:06.097 --> 05:08.753
I know he wants to buy
my share of the apartment.

05:08.793 --> 05:11.100
And I offered him
a very reasonable price, right?

05:30.660 --> 05:34.761
Check-out the average price
per square yard in the 7th district.

05:38.398 --> 05:41.428
Yes, I am indulgent,
but I'm not stupid.

05:41.467 --> 05:43.121
I know that I'd lose out.

05:43.848 --> 05:45.201
I have to talk to you.

05:45.277 --> 05:47.737
You know the law
better than I do, right?

05:47.920 --> 05:50.446
Nobody is being forced
to stay in that area.

05:50.500 --> 05:52.893
I know, I heard.
Just a second ago.

05:52.980 --> 05:56.566
Um... I know, I know.
I haven't told her yet. But, um...

05:57.132 --> 05:58.792
As soon as I can, okay?

05:58.843 --> 06:00.609
I got it.
Yeah.

06:04.428 --> 06:08.504
If your client wants to sell and split up
the money, I have no problem with that.

06:08.551 --> 06:12.018
We'll give it to an agency tomorrow
and see what the market's like.

06:12.271 --> 06:15.327
WILHEM HAS DIED

06:34.352 --> 06:36.862
Yeah, there's really nothing
on the net yet, Just...

06:37.002 --> 06:39.648
Just this press release, and um...

06:40.881 --> 06:42.191
comments.

06:42.477 --> 06:44.565
What kind of comments?

06:44.705 --> 06:46.518
Hmm, you do not want to know...

06:46.686 --> 06:49.420
They're stupid.
It just says, you know...

06:50.699 --> 06:52.119
From Zorglub228:

06:52.239 --> 06:53.715
"I thought he died a while ago.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.257
Besides, he hasn't written anything
of interest in 20 years."

06:56.329 --> 06:59.298
WiseGuy666:
"Nobody pays much attention to writers,"

06:59.335 --> 07:03.032
"People die all over the world
and no-one ever mentions them."

07:04.008 --> 07:05.601
ZoraRose:

07:05.862 --> 07:10.289
"Didn't know who this guys was."
But, offers her condolences to the family.

07:13.164 --> 07:14.918
So, I-I spoke to Urs Kobler.

07:15.078 --> 07:17.092
We canceled the press, obviously.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.244
Menor can help me get it tonight.

07:19.724 --> 07:21.525
It's, it's gonna be really...

07:21.734 --> 07:22.744
different.

07:22.823 --> 07:24.582
It'll be gloomy

07:24.864 --> 07:26.346
Official and stiff.

07:26.424 --> 07:28.346
Everything Wilhelm hated.

07:28.563 --> 07:30.364
Yeah, people are gonna be sad.

07:30.873 --> 07:32.923
What do you expect?
He's...

07:34.219 --> 07:35.559
He's dead.

07:35.859 --> 07:39.605
If I wanted to be true to him,
I'd turn around and go home.

07:39.769 --> 07:41.668
I think you'll find the words
once you're there.

07:41.694 --> 07:43.490
I think they'll come naturally.
I think...

07:43.544 --> 07:44.897
I know.

07:45.260 --> 07:46.916
Who could do him justice
better than you?

07:46.963 --> 07:48.247
A stranger?

07:49.850 --> 07:51.050
You love him.

07:51.117 --> 07:52.510
That's different.

07:52.950 --> 07:54.430
I love him.

07:56.642 --> 07:59.146
I know so little about him.

08:00.562 --> 08:03.082
Um, you know,
you know what I mean.

08:03.558 --> 08:05.525
If you want to be true to him,...

08:06.525 --> 08:08.324
you have to spear on.

08:11.236 --> 08:12.409
Hello?

08:15.506 --> 08:17.401
Um... sure.

08:17.575 --> 08:20.089
Yeah, we're on a train,
so we might lose you, but I'll...

08:20.222 --> 08:21.562
I'll ask her.

08:25.492 --> 08:28.282
- It's France Inter.
- Oh, God.

08:30.736 --> 08:33.703
You kinda have to.
I'm sorry.

08:35.832 --> 08:36.859
Yes.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.193
Yes, with Maria Enders.

08:40.619 --> 08:42.399
Yes, I know.
Thanks.

08:52.341 --> 08:56.888
WILHEM MELCHIOR

09:00.677 --> 09:03.224
A sequel to Maloja Snake?

09:05.077 --> 09:07.323
Yes, he talked about it.

09:09.043 --> 09:12.949
He wanted me to play Sigrid
20 years later.

09:13.600 --> 09:17.027
But, I do not know
what he had in mind.

09:17.699 --> 09:21.819
He was very vague;
so I dont really know his idea.

09:24.801 --> 09:26.741
I regret it.

09:29.834 --> 09:31.554
Of course, I am sorry.

09:35.085 --> 09:36.365
Rosa just called.

09:36.665 --> 09:38.343
I, I'll call her right back.

09:38.391 --> 09:40.488
She's actually not gonna be
available 'til tonight.

09:40.540 --> 09:42.188
She's really busy.
She...

09:42.848 --> 09:45.072
She's supposed to go to the morgue.

09:45.498 --> 09:47.374
You find out everything?

09:47.685 --> 09:49.218
Yeah.
Um...

09:51.077 --> 09:53.313
Wilhem was home...
in Sils Maria.

09:53.364 --> 09:56.227
Rosa went for a check-up in Basel.

09:56.555 --> 09:58.925
She thinks that he was home
all day writing, as usual,

09:58.965 --> 10:00.422
went for a late afternoon walk,

10:00.455 --> 10:03.065
but she called to check on him,
and couldn't get through.

10:03.098 --> 10:05.268
So she got worried,
and sent the neighbors over.

10:05.301 --> 10:06.974
Doors were locked.
The lights were out.

10:07.021 --> 10:08.434
He wasn't home.

10:10.666 --> 10:12.402
When did they find him?

10:12.464 --> 10:16.416
Late afternoon,
like in the middle of nowhere...

10:16.487 --> 10:18.382
They think it was a heart attack.

10:56.287 --> 10:58.600
It's so exciting having you here.

10:59.220 --> 11:00.480
Nice.

11:01.116 --> 11:03.752
The cockroaches must've
taken a later train.

11:06.539 --> 11:08.159
Join us at the hotel.

11:08.266 --> 11:09.732
Yes, see you there.

11:11.540 --> 11:15.116
You are uh...
at a loss for words.

11:15.526 --> 11:19.129
I have to say, my first reaction
was to head right back.

11:19.882 --> 11:21.556
I understand.

11:22.128 --> 11:25.878
We were wondering is that
should we move forward or...

11:25.912 --> 11:27.752
cancel everything?

11:28.093 --> 11:30.400
You know, here in Switzerland,

11:30.467 --> 11:34.394
we are not big on public
displays of anything.

11:35.753 --> 11:37.442
Especially grief.

11:37.870 --> 11:40.467
This should have been a celebration.

11:40.520 --> 11:44.067
And now it will be
a posthumous homage.

11:44.108 --> 11:46.671
It's gonna generate the kind
of press that we do not want.

11:46.771 --> 11:48.759
We'll try to keep them at distance.

11:48.784 --> 11:51.217
Paparazzi are gonna be all over her.
You realize that, right?

11:51.311 --> 11:52.932
I have to think it over.

11:53.821 --> 11:57.046
Everything's hitting me at once;
so, I, I, I,... I don't know.

11:57.125 --> 12:00.948
Of course.
That's why we invited Henryk Wald.

12:02.347 --> 12:04.005
Henryk Wald?!

12:04.685 --> 12:05.762
Yes.

12:07.224 --> 12:10.328
He's devastated as well;
but, he agreed

12:10.368 --> 12:13.694
to hop on a plane
to be with us tonight.

12:14.347 --> 12:18.654
If you prefer not to accept the prize,
Henryk can do it.

12:18.821 --> 12:20.327
It's up to you.

12:20.775 --> 12:23.950
He's associated with
Wilhelm's theatre.

12:24.003 --> 12:26.590
Most of the plays
were written for him.

12:27.866 --> 12:29.219
You don't appreciate him?

12:29.248 --> 12:31.152
We did two films together.

12:31.220 --> 12:33.492
No, we didn't get along very well.

12:34.072 --> 12:35.931
But, I'm glad he's here.

12:36.782 --> 12:40.235
He and Wilhelm were very close
and Rosa likes him a lot.

12:40.517 --> 12:44.287
He's a...
a great actor.

12:44.360 --> 12:45.487
Yeah.

12:46.060 --> 12:48.336
One last question...

12:48.430 --> 12:50.483
Oh God, I forgot to tell you
these things, right?

12:50.510 --> 12:51.656
Chanel.

12:51.770 --> 12:52.803
Chanel.

12:52.845 --> 12:55.876
The press attachÃ© from Chanel
is waiting for you at the hotel,

12:55.931 --> 12:57.748
to try on your gown.

12:57.802 --> 13:00.977
- You don't have to.
- No, you do not have to.

13:09.154 --> 13:10.930
You can turn this off?

13:15.027 --> 13:17.170
And no fruit.
Thank you.

13:35.501 --> 13:37.848
Okay, all good.
Thank you.

13:43.726 --> 13:45.933
So, what do you think?
Will she stay?

13:45.970 --> 13:47.206
Yeah, she'll... she'll stay.

13:47.251 --> 13:49.633
Because if not,
I have to change the tickets.

13:49.673 --> 13:51.673
I know, she'll stay.
Trust me.

13:52.294 --> 13:53.702
Thank you.

13:55.887 --> 13:58.421
I can't deal with this.
It's impossible.

13:59.056 --> 14:01.439
I'll never find the right words.

14:03.981 --> 14:07.737
His body isn't even cold yet,
and everybody wants a piece of him.

14:07.771 --> 14:09.430
Starting with Henryk Wald,
of course.

14:09.517 --> 14:12.077
Of course he'd be happy
to accept the prize.

14:13.548 --> 14:15.871
The premier could just not see him.

14:16.453 --> 14:17.739
Henryk?

14:18.145 --> 14:20.013
Why are you still
so upset with him?

14:20.095 --> 14:23.008
I have no reason to have
stopped being upset with him.

14:23.085 --> 14:24.971
So, he was, like, in love
with you or something?

14:25.010 --> 14:26.813
Not at all.
He was just uh...

14:26.867 --> 14:29.306
furious I didn't give in to him.

14:30.640 --> 14:33.816
He's perverse, violent.
He hits women.

14:34.585 --> 14:36.823
He likes to humiliate them.

14:37.050 --> 14:38.956
Look it up on the internet.

14:39.561 --> 14:41.872
I thought we despised the internet.

14:43.379 --> 14:44.425
Caroline?

14:44.465 --> 14:45.741
Hey.
Valentine.

14:45.781 --> 14:46.791
Hello

14:46.818 --> 14:47.824
- Hi.
- Hi.

14:47.849 --> 14:49.169
Thanks for agreeing to do this.

14:49.209 --> 14:51.461
I know this must be
really difficult for you.

15:00.419 --> 15:01.646
Uh, this is Berndt.

15:01.699 --> 15:03.274
- Oh, hi.
- Hi.

15:03.312 --> 15:04.579
Very pleased to meet you.

15:04.606 --> 15:05.888
- Nice to meet you.
- You know, those really...

15:05.922 --> 15:08.161
thrashy photos I showed you
of Lindsay Lohan?

15:08.488 --> 15:10.202
This guy's responsible.

15:10.453 --> 15:12.606
But, I'll try to be
more elegant today.

16:25.856 --> 16:27.299
It's Rosa.

16:30.044 --> 16:31.661
Am I bothering you?

16:31.976 --> 16:34.567
I just wanted to tell you...

16:35.859 --> 16:37.280
to thank you.

16:37.823 --> 16:40.623
It's good that you are there.
It's good...

16:41.895 --> 16:44.607
that you're accepting the prize.

16:44.749 --> 16:46.792
It's what Wilhelm wanted.

16:49.256 --> 16:52.712
Henryk?
No, he couldn't know.

16:53.006 --> 16:55.298
What he thought of Henryk?

16:56.217 --> 16:58.043
"The less he understands,
the better he is.

16:58.070 --> 17:00.798
When he understands nothing,
he's excellent!"

17:04.813 --> 17:07.866
I would like to give your a hug,
but,...

17:08.242 --> 17:09.736
I'm leaving.

17:10.617 --> 17:15.226
I can't stand being alone in Sils.
It's too difficult.

17:16.111 --> 17:19.358
But, there is something I...
want you...

17:19.439 --> 17:22.339
and... only you...

17:28.547 --> 17:31.128
to...
to know...

17:42.285 --> 17:45.413
So, he knew about
the illness for very long time?

17:49.068 --> 17:52.100
Did the autopsy say
what he swallowed?

17:54.781 --> 17:56.841
Oh, I see.

17:57.426 --> 17:59.681
He left nothing to chance.

18:00.815 --> 18:02.218
Beautiful.

18:02.478 --> 18:04.831
Turn your body a bit
sideways, please? Yep.

18:05.018 --> 18:08.971
Chin, chin up a little bit, please.
Thank you. Great. Yep.

18:09.114 --> 18:10.664
- Maria?
- Hmm?

18:10.814 --> 18:12.660
Sorry, it's uh...

18:12.727 --> 18:14.734
- your future ex.
- A little bit. Alright.

18:14.833 --> 18:16.829
- Hold on a second.
- Right, right. Okay.

18:16.920 --> 18:18.632
Hello?
Hello?!

18:20.589 --> 18:24.629
Spare me the somber tone.
I'm not the one who died.

18:25.214 --> 18:28.854
Yes, I know that Wilhelm's dead.
I'm in Zurich now.

18:42.431 --> 18:43.951
Maria!

18:45.351 --> 18:46.631
Maria!

18:46.806 --> 18:48.267
- This way!
- Maria!

18:48.301 --> 18:49.661
- This way.
- Maria!

18:49.709 --> 18:50.776
Maria!

18:51.204 --> 18:53.384
- The press is all here.
- I know.

18:53.430 --> 18:55.684
Are we to put them all in?

18:57.066 --> 19:00.862
What you need to know is that
we met very early at University,

19:00.919 --> 19:03.519
we proposed studying
literature and theology.

19:04.356 --> 19:05.609
Hey.

19:05.839 --> 19:08.742
And I had the privilege
of acting in all of his plays,...

19:08.782 --> 19:10.087
here and abroad.

19:10.142 --> 19:13.462
He had become reclusive,
mysterious, and inaccessible.

19:13.505 --> 19:16.081
Wilhelm was the simplest
man in the world.

19:16.841 --> 19:20.312
He liked to ski in the winter,
and go hiking in the summer.

19:20.752 --> 19:23.312
Those are the fondest
memories I have of him.

19:23.352 --> 19:26.845
His later work depicts a bleak,
destructive vision.

19:26.881 --> 19:29.299
I acted in those plays.

19:31.261 --> 19:34.927
It's true.
At times, I found them scary.

19:38.612 --> 19:41.575
A sea of gray hair.

19:43.248 --> 19:44.517
Completely.

19:45.804 --> 19:47.005
So, uh...

19:47.072 --> 19:49.200
First, I say a few words.

19:49.247 --> 19:51.474
I hope I'm up to the task.

19:51.547 --> 19:53.434
And then I introduce Henryk.

19:53.475 --> 19:57.105
Once he has finished,
he asks you to join him on stage.

19:57.151 --> 19:59.705
You introduce the film.
That's it.

20:14.505 --> 20:17.007
I saw Wilhelm two weeks ago.

20:18.831 --> 20:20.523
We went hunting.

20:22.168 --> 20:25.864
He was his usual self.
There, but not there.

20:28.989 --> 20:32.360
He mentioned the prize and
said he wouldn't be attending.

20:33.465 --> 20:35.892
I told him he'd miss
an opportunity to see you.

20:35.925 --> 20:37.952
I was on Long Island
six months ago.

20:38.025 --> 20:40.048
I spent a week with him and Rose.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.103
I know.

20:41.129 --> 20:43.283
I don't give a fuck
that you know.

20:44.137 --> 20:46.576
Henryk, you're almost on.

20:46.902 --> 20:49.132
- We should really go.
- Would you excuse me?

20:49.832 --> 20:51.825
Of course, it's time.

20:54.394 --> 20:57.381
We had an affair when
we were shooting Maloja Snake.

20:57.425 --> 20:58.795
Yeah, I couldn't tell.

20:58.824 --> 21:00.884
Well, I was 18 and kinda dumb.

21:00.982 --> 21:03.023
And he really took advantage.

21:03.804 --> 21:06.070
After the shoot,
I never heard from him.

21:06.204 --> 21:07.784
It destroyed me.

21:07.850 --> 21:09.964
I'm sure you've run into him since.

21:10.584 --> 21:13.218
We made another film
together afterwards.

21:14.184 --> 21:16.398
- Which one?
- Oh, you don't want to know.

21:16.458 --> 21:18.116
Tolstoy adaptation.

21:18.170 --> 21:19.648
German producers.

21:20.354 --> 21:21.728
Who cares?

21:22.112 --> 21:26.477
Well ten years later, I was famous.
Then he was interested.

21:26.648 --> 21:29.618
And he kept harassing me,
calling me in the middle of the night.

21:29.808 --> 21:32.837
I did not give in,
and that he hated.

21:32.979 --> 21:36.494
And he made me pay for it
every single day of the shooting.

21:37.227 --> 21:39.834
He was really amazing
in that one movie, um...

21:40.487 --> 21:41.918
What is it called?

21:42.525 --> 21:46.645
He plays a... Soviet defector
with, like, missile codes and shit?

21:46.725 --> 21:48.991
- Um... You know?
- No Idea. No, I don't know.

21:49.049 --> 21:50.735
Never heard of it.

21:51.385 --> 21:52.799
He's great in it.

21:53.701 --> 21:55.121
He's so intense.

21:55.155 --> 21:57.828
Especially, in the more physical scenes.
That stare...

21:57.898 --> 22:00.414
He is like, Ppp.
I like him.

22:00.455 --> 22:01.954
Yeah, I kind of got it.

22:02.124 --> 22:04.508
I mean, as an actor,
I really like him.

22:12.791 --> 22:17.041
<i>And unfortunately,
he has to leave tomorrow morning.</i>

22:17.148 --> 22:19.214
<i>Henryk Wald!</i>

22:23.411 --> 22:25.321
<i>Thank you.
Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

22:25.382 --> 22:28.747
Four years ago,
I was here on this stage...

22:29.121 --> 22:33.392
<i>for the premiere of the Reichstag,
by Wilhelm Melchior.</i>

22:35.080 --> 22:38.916
<i>I did not know then that
it would be his last work.</i>

22:39.370 --> 22:43.813
<i>He sat in the third row
and stared at me.</i>

22:45.020 --> 22:47.646
<i>I had never acted so badly.</i>

22:48.058 --> 22:50.701
Maria, you're on in five minutes.

22:52.887 --> 22:56.503
<i>Wilhelm Melchior
will always be with us,...</i>

22:56.657 --> 22:58.177
<i>through his works.</i>

22:58.722 --> 23:01.902
- Maria, you wait in there.
- I had the privilege to work for him...

23:01.942 --> 23:04.549
here in London and elsewhere.

23:04.668 --> 23:07.934
So, I don't say "goodbye", only...

23:08.087 --> 23:09.981
"see you soon", Wilhelm.

23:12.679 --> 23:16.839
Thank you, Henryk,
for the beautiful tribute.

23:16.922 --> 23:19.758
Let's now welcome
an old friend of Wilhelm,

23:19.795 --> 23:22.532
who came just for this occasion.

23:22.585 --> 23:24.858
Please, give your
heartfelt applause for...

23:24.930 --> 23:26.807
Maria Enders.

23:39.366 --> 23:40.644
Thank you.

23:43.582 --> 23:45.307
Go get them, tiger.

23:46.691 --> 23:48.524
Thank you very much.

24:07.821 --> 24:09.961
- Hi.
- Good evening. Welcome.

24:12.115 --> 24:14.062
I'm honored to welcome you here.

24:14.175 --> 24:17.022
I wish it had been under
happier circumstances.

24:17.375 --> 24:18.682
It's...

24:19.390 --> 24:22.336
It's great to celebrate his work,
especially today.

24:22.443 --> 24:26.159
I was eager that the city
of Zurich pay tribute to him.

24:26.383 --> 24:29.079
He was very grateful to you.
He told me so.

24:31.698 --> 24:32.764
Hey.

24:32.858 --> 24:34.190
She'll just be two seconds.

24:34.238 --> 24:37.218
I'm sure she's gonna be thrilled
to be relieved of officialdom.

24:37.582 --> 24:39.663
You know that
his last play was set in Zurich?

24:39.711 --> 24:41.009
Oh, yes.

24:41.283 --> 24:44.256
He paints an idle portrait
of our political class.

24:44.290 --> 24:45.416
That's an understatement.

24:45.449 --> 24:49.109
You should know.
Your character was evil.

24:49.395 --> 24:51.201
Klaus Diesterweg
is here to see you.

24:53.155 --> 24:55.183
Excuse.
I'm sorry.

24:57.819 --> 24:59.463
I already told him "no".

24:59.799 --> 25:01.402
He's here just to see you.

25:01.434 --> 25:03.468
The project doesn't
interest me, okay?

25:03.502 --> 25:05.914
He's a great director,
just hear him out.

25:05.962 --> 25:07.046
You don't have to do it.

25:07.073 --> 25:08.619
He's probably the best for generation.

25:08.649 --> 25:11.259
I know.
We saw the same production.

25:11.369 --> 25:14.023
I mean, if you'd like to go on chatting
with the Mayor and Henryk,

25:14.056 --> 25:15.623
then, be my guest.

25:17.471 --> 25:18.927
No, thank you.

25:22.941 --> 25:24.724
Hi, do you mind
if I cut out for a bit?

25:25.251 --> 25:27.764
- I'm just gonna go meet Berndt.
- Berndt?

25:27.844 --> 25:29.364
The photographer.

25:30.797 --> 25:32.610
I'm just gonna find
somewhere a bit livelier.

25:32.635 --> 25:34.316
- This place hasn't had some.
- Hmm.

25:34.363 --> 25:36.898
No problem.
I don't plan to hang around.

25:37.044 --> 25:38.487
Enjoy.

25:42.987 --> 25:44.534
Thank you for finding
some time for me.

25:44.560 --> 25:45.713
It's a pleasure to meet you.

25:45.747 --> 25:47.707
- I hope you don't find me too insistent.
- No, not at all.

25:47.747 --> 25:49.593
I've seen quite a few
of your productions.

25:49.627 --> 25:51.441
I... enjoy them.
And...

25:51.797 --> 25:54.940
I know we'll find an opportunity
to work together...

25:55.000 --> 25:56.333
in the future.

25:56.468 --> 25:58.133
Give me one more chance.

25:58.435 --> 25:59.767
Klaus...

26:03.034 --> 26:06.087
I played Sigrid
in Maloja Snake...

26:06.414 --> 26:08.074
when he was 18.

26:08.174 --> 26:10.394
For me,
it was more than a role. And...

26:11.444 --> 26:13.700
in some way,
I am still Sigrid.

26:13.748 --> 26:14.917
That's my point.

26:14.957 --> 26:16.373
Sigrid seduces Helena...

26:16.407 --> 26:18.708
And it has nothing to do with
being a lesbian, by the way.

26:18.733 --> 26:20.227
I've always been straight.

26:20.300 --> 26:21.827
That's not at all what I meant.

26:21.867 --> 26:25.090
Sigrid is free...
beyond everything, and...

26:25.123 --> 26:26.623
most of all,
she's destructive,

26:26.657 --> 26:28.583
- unpredictable...
- I know.

26:29.947 --> 26:33.487
And right or wrong,
I've always identified with that freedom.

26:34.442 --> 26:36.229
It's a way of uh...

26:37.636 --> 26:39.436
protecting myself.

26:39.765 --> 26:41.002
Do you smoke?

26:41.349 --> 26:42.933
Uh, no, no.

26:43.329 --> 26:44.942
I try not to.

26:47.593 --> 26:50.060
And for you,
Helena embodies the opposite?

26:50.122 --> 26:52.620
Helena's 40.
She runs a company.

26:52.788 --> 26:56.128
She falls, head over heels, in love
with a girl who doesn't love her.

26:56.604 --> 26:58.165
And woos to suicide.

26:58.264 --> 27:00.964
Yes, she's completely the opposite.

27:01.276 --> 27:05.474
But, what is it that attracts Helena
to Sigrid if they are so different?

27:05.601 --> 27:06.940
It's obvious.

27:07.733 --> 27:09.179
Her youth.

27:09.645 --> 27:11.973
Well, if you're telling me that
I'm Helena's age now,

27:12.013 --> 27:13.826
yeah, you're right.
It's true.

27:14.379 --> 27:16.635
But, that doesn't mean
I can play her.

27:16.684 --> 27:19.175
The way I see Helena
is totally different.

27:19.331 --> 27:23.154
Despite her Bourgeois life,
despite her responsibilities,

27:23.196 --> 27:25.661
she's not the epitome of order.

27:25.694 --> 27:27.954
And not at all,
the opposite of Sigrid.

27:28.034 --> 27:32.647
No, she is married, with children.
Her social life is a huge success,

27:32.730 --> 27:35.626
And she sacrifices it all.
Yeah, she's destructive.

27:35.673 --> 27:39.506
Sigrid reviles this hidden violence
in Helena.

27:39.546 --> 27:41.909
What a "hidden" or "tamed"?

27:44.189 --> 27:46.795
Time's gone by and
she can't accept it.

27:47.142 --> 27:48.862
Me, neither, I guess.

27:51.274 --> 27:53.036
There's no antagonism.

27:53.145 --> 27:56.104
It's the attraction of two women
with the same wound.

27:56.648 --> 27:59.534
Sigrid and Helena are one
and the same person.

27:59.700 --> 28:01.668
One and the same person.

28:02.080 --> 28:04.046
That's what the play is about.

28:05.687 --> 28:09.121
And because you were Sigrid,
only you can be Helena now.

28:09.274 --> 28:11.977
Hmm, how can you be so sure?

28:12.342 --> 28:15.305
You know as well as I do that
Wilhelm Melchior...

28:15.358 --> 28:17.305
had been working on
a sequel for years.

28:17.358 --> 28:18.541
Yes.

28:18.615 --> 28:21.515
But, it was about Sigrid
at 40 years old.

28:21.571 --> 28:25.328
No, it was about Sigrid,
20 years later became Helena.

28:29.254 --> 28:31.885
So, who's gonna play Sigrid?

28:32.751 --> 28:34.365
Jo-Ann Ellis.

28:36.179 --> 28:39.446
She did a super-hero movie
that just opened in the States.

28:39.707 --> 28:41.147
And besides that?

28:41.188 --> 28:43.184
Not much..
She has nineteen.

28:43.397 --> 28:46.750
She's a lot more interesting
than her interviews and profiles.

28:46.851 --> 28:48.727
She has a theatrical background.

28:48.789 --> 28:52.142
She doesn't want to be
swallowed-up by Hollywood.

28:52.931 --> 28:57.144
She admires you and she's willing
to pull out of her other commitments.

29:01.773 --> 29:05.057
Well now,
I've listened carefully.

29:06.736 --> 29:09.744
But to be honest, um...
the role scares me.

29:09.798 --> 29:11.444
Helena scares me.

29:11.494 --> 29:13.664
I'm in the middle of a divorce.

29:13.971 --> 29:16.733
I feel alone and vulnerable.

29:17.124 --> 29:19.694
Probably, too vulnerable to do this.

29:20.769 --> 29:23.489
If you refuse,
I understand; but,...

29:24.556 --> 29:26.886
it will be a missed opportunity.

29:27.465 --> 29:29.422
Especially, for Wilhelm.

29:31.524 --> 29:33.237
I should get going.

29:36.221 --> 29:37.474
Must be nice...

29:41.103 --> 29:44.086
Excuse me;
but, I won't be staying for dinner.

29:45.788 --> 29:47.539
Good evening, Maria.

29:48.018 --> 29:49.437
Klaus?

29:50.197 --> 29:51.984
I have another reason.

29:52.192 --> 29:53.801
Susan Rosenberg.

29:54.509 --> 29:56.522
She played Helena with me.

29:56.582 --> 29:58.722
I remember Susan Rosenberg.

29:59.136 --> 30:02.062
She died in a car accident
a year after.

30:03.588 --> 30:05.217
It's just a superstition,
I've um...

30:05.258 --> 30:08.631
always associated her death
with Helena's suicide.

30:08.677 --> 30:11.937
She was a lousy actress who didn't
understand a thing about the role,

30:14.191 --> 30:16.378
And her conventional style of acting

30:16.413 --> 30:19.438
highlighted the modernity
of your feal performance.

30:19.685 --> 30:21.536
You should be grateful to her.

30:31.504 --> 30:33.451
Please, sit down.

30:34.795 --> 30:36.235
Excuse me.

30:39.652 --> 30:42.835
Oh, is there a way of changing this?
Put him uh...

30:42.890 --> 30:45.462
I'm, I'm sorry.
Oh, he's coming.

30:56.436 --> 30:57.909
Thank you, sir.

31:01.380 --> 31:03.374
You were with Klaus Diesterweg.

31:03.557 --> 31:05.637
Are you going to accept his offer?

31:05.698 --> 31:06.840
What offer?

31:06.881 --> 31:07.974
You know.

31:08.043 --> 31:09.606
He's a very good director.

31:09.659 --> 31:12.293
If he offered me a role,
I'd accept it on the spot.

31:12.390 --> 31:15.359
So, that means, um...
I should accept it?

31:15.438 --> 31:17.078
God, no!

31:19.622 --> 31:23.068
There's much talk
about sequel of his.

31:24.075 --> 31:26.255
Remember, he had never finished it.

31:26.382 --> 31:27.889
Sorry for being brutal.

31:28.102 --> 31:29.615
But, I am a simple man...

31:29.729 --> 31:31.782
and the play tells a simple story.

31:32.030 --> 31:34.749
An older woman falls in love
with a scheming girl

31:34.775 --> 31:36.719
that has her wrapped
around her little finger.

31:37.042 --> 31:38.962
The girl takes advantage of her,...

31:39.029 --> 31:41.352
squeezes everything
she can out of her,...

31:41.498 --> 31:42.992
then dumps her.

31:43.078 --> 31:45.834
Helena's love for Sigrid
makes her stupid.

31:45.878 --> 31:49.187
And blind to what everybody in
the audience can see right away.

31:49.421 --> 31:52.851
But then, that's really all
she's ever wanted.

31:53.537 --> 31:56.657
She's fascinated by her own downfall.

31:56.804 --> 31:58.677
It's as clear as day.

31:59.111 --> 32:01.304
That's why the play was such a hit.

32:01.337 --> 32:03.657
It is still being performed today.

32:05.701 --> 32:07.741
Why stage it...

32:07.801 --> 32:11.707
- if you want to tell another story?
- I think your reading is simplistic.

32:12.502 --> 32:14.369
I know Sigrid, and...

32:15.196 --> 32:17.592
believe me, she's more
interesting than that.

32:17.652 --> 32:23.599
Yes, she takes advantage of Helena.
Yes, she fascinates her, and she knows it.

32:24.375 --> 32:26.315
Well, you can decide
not to look in further,

32:26.362 --> 32:28.712
but, I had to,
because I played her.

32:28.794 --> 32:31.405
You're just talking about
what's on the surface.

32:32.285 --> 32:35.515
The play's about what
attracts them to each other. Hence,...

32:35.608 --> 32:38.401
it's harder to see,
and it's more profound, and...

32:38.687 --> 32:39.788
truer.

32:40.858 --> 32:43.659
The impossibility of
their relationship is

32:43.693 --> 32:45.639
as cruel for Sigrid.

32:46.034 --> 32:47.739
Cruel for Sigrid?

32:48.118 --> 32:49.558
I'm sure she'll get over it.

32:49.584 --> 32:50.977
What do you know?

32:51.037 --> 32:52.731
Time.
Youth.

32:53.064 --> 32:54.925
She has her life ahead of her

32:54.975 --> 32:57.345
Well, Helena's young too,
I mean, she's not old.

32:57.387 --> 32:59.147
She has her life ahead of her too.

32:59.194 --> 33:00.781
But, she decides to give it all up.

33:00.815 --> 33:02.978
Helena is not used to
being turned down.

33:03.378 --> 33:07.171
She's discovered her own frailty
and she can't accept it.

33:20.753 --> 33:23.744
We'll drop Mr. Wald off first,
please.

33:25.015 --> 33:27.371
Grand Hôtel du Lac,
please.

33:31.306 --> 33:33.732
So, Klaus has persuaded you?

33:34.151 --> 33:35.970
You're going to play Helena.

33:37.445 --> 33:39.298
I didn't say that.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.712
But, I'm considering it.

33:42.223 --> 33:43.650
Yes.

33:56.598 --> 33:59.768
Are you sure you don't
want to have a last drink?

34:03.963 --> 34:07.156
I'm already drunk,...
darling.

34:11.985 --> 34:13.409
Henryk!

34:14.388 --> 34:15.788
Hold on.

34:23.563 --> 34:25.360
ROOM 339

34:53.014 --> 34:54.364
HENRYK WALD

35:24.470 --> 35:26.328
JO ANN ELLIS

35:40.770 --> 35:43.304
PART TWO

36:22.306 --> 36:23.594
Wow!

36:24.088 --> 36:25.481
Hey.

36:25.871 --> 36:27.898
I've just found the main road again.
I'm sorry.

36:27.938 --> 36:29.551
I must've set the GPS wrong.

36:29.598 --> 36:32.065
Like, in an hour or so, probably.

36:32.876 --> 36:34.134
I had a um...

36:34.556 --> 36:35.848
dream um...

36:37.910 --> 36:39.986
We were rehearsing,
and the...

36:40.026 --> 36:43.373
past and the present
were blending together.

36:44.297 --> 36:45.864
I'm confused.

36:46.124 --> 36:47.581
No kidding.

36:48.190 --> 36:50.753
I should not have said "yes" to Klaus.

36:51.246 --> 36:52.379
But,...

36:52.499 --> 36:55.569
Wilhelm's death mourning,
I couldn't refuse.

36:55.636 --> 36:57.636
He is a "sick" director.

36:58.349 --> 37:01.029
Jo-Ann is a super star.
It pays well.

37:01.780 --> 37:03.591
I don't need the money.

37:06.143 --> 37:07.316
Okay.

37:31.354 --> 37:32.634
Hi.

37:38.303 --> 37:40.257
Stay as long as you want.

37:40.553 --> 37:43.313
I like the fact
that you are walking

37:43.439 --> 37:46.099
in the part here
where it was written.

37:47.029 --> 37:50.082
You promised.
No ghosts.

37:50.802 --> 37:52.982
No, there aren't any.

37:53.140 --> 37:54.947
I was joking!

37:54.993 --> 37:58.239
No, it was half joking.

38:46.206 --> 38:48.899
This is what I wanted to show you.

38:49.015 --> 38:51.515
This is where Wilhelm killed himself.

38:51.695 --> 38:55.229
But, that... that stays...
between you and me.

38:59.981 --> 39:02.728
Is that the Maloja pass, over there?

39:02.774 --> 39:03.968
Yeah.

39:04.064 --> 39:06.344
- The Snake, right?
- The Snake.

39:06.391 --> 39:09.064
- Why a "snake" in the play? It's uh...
- Yeah.

39:09.471 --> 39:11.244
It's ambiguous.

39:11.889 --> 39:13.765
The Maloja snake.

39:14.419 --> 39:17.273
It's a cloud formation.

39:17.385 --> 39:19.322
Fairly rare.

39:19.396 --> 39:21.309
Virtually unexplained.

39:21.396 --> 39:24.496
It's a sign...
of bad weather.

39:25.404 --> 39:28.594
And the clouds,
they are coming from the Italian lakes,...

39:28.757 --> 39:30.400
over the pass,...

39:30.567 --> 39:33.534
and winding through the Valley...

39:34.024 --> 39:35.970
like a serpent.

39:36.895 --> 39:40.071
Therefore, it's a snake.
They call it a snake.

39:40.207 --> 39:43.589
THE CLOUD PHENOMENON OF MALOJA

39:50.695 --> 39:53.488
FORESHADOWINGS

40:00.437 --> 40:03.954
THE CLOUDS RISE OVER THE PASS OF MALOJA

40:13.317 --> 40:15.761
THE SO-CALLED MALOJA SNAKE

40:26.081 --> 40:28.811
Wilhelm was fascinated
by this film.

40:29.163 --> 40:33.937
He used to marvel at the fact that
the true nature of the landscape...

40:33.990 --> 40:37.563
revealed itself in these images.

40:39.245 --> 40:40.685
Yeah, um...

40:41.045 --> 40:44.118
But, the black and white
creates a distance,

40:44.298 --> 40:47.040
It sets the passing of time.

40:47.540 --> 40:50.667
It's almost a century old.

40:50.907 --> 40:54.843
Actually, it
comes from very far away.

40:55.095 --> 40:57.273
That's the beauty of it.

41:12.235 --> 41:14.376
- Thank you so much!
- Nice to meet you. Thank you.

41:14.422 --> 41:16.114
Thank you.

41:19.080 --> 41:22.654
I won't promise to come and
see you off in London.

41:22.814 --> 41:25.087
I hope you change your mind,
all right?

41:26.957 --> 41:29.316
It is only theater.

41:32.572 --> 41:33.948
Oh, Maria!

41:35.426 --> 41:37.866
This belonged to Wilhelm.

41:38.573 --> 41:40.126
Keep it.

41:59.639 --> 42:02.106
Well, you were 18 years old.
You weren't a child.

42:02.261 --> 42:05.379
There had to have been
some kind of attraction in her.

42:06.537 --> 42:08.854
Wilhelm was far from a saint, right?

42:11.181 --> 42:12.889
- No.
- Maybe.

42:15.587 --> 42:17.074
Hmm!

