You're jealous.

59:54.656 --> 59:55.845
Jealousy?

59:57.295 --> 59:58.502
I don't know.

59:58.723 --> 01:00:00.020
My time.

01:00:00.876 --> 01:00:02.068
My thoughts.

01:00:03.395 --> 01:00:04.721
Maybe, my affection.

01:00:04.781 --> 01:00:06.832
No, I'm not jealous.

01:00:06.905 --> 01:00:08.961
I'm thrilled that
you have a boyfriend.

01:00:09.185 --> 01:00:10.868
There haven't been that many.

01:00:11.483 --> 01:00:14.658
And when there is one,
you burn through him pretty fast.

01:00:16.024 --> 01:00:18.377
- I'll tell you.
- No, you won't.

01:00:18.793 --> 01:00:22.706
And I never know if I should believe
what little you do tell me.

01:00:23.362 --> 01:00:24.779
It's you.

01:00:30.575 --> 01:00:33.120
Why the fuck are we doing this?

01:01:01.982 --> 01:01:04.203
Can you pass me those?
I'm a little late.

01:01:07.563 --> 01:01:08.583
Sorry.

01:01:08.667 --> 01:01:09.917
See you.

01:02:32.727 --> 01:02:35.707
We can do anything.
But, you did sign a contract.

01:02:35.747 --> 01:02:37.012
Pulling out will cost you.

01:02:37.052 --> 01:02:38.957
You know,
I thought it over,

01:02:38.990 --> 01:02:41.110
I worked on the scene,
I can't.

01:02:41.159 --> 01:02:42.913
I mean, I can, but...

01:02:43.122 --> 01:02:44.282
It... it's too hard.

01:02:44.331 --> 01:02:46.229
I feel too much resent for Helena.

01:02:46.269 --> 01:02:47.433
I am Sigrid!

01:02:47.499 --> 01:02:49.190
I want to stay Sigrid!

01:02:49.244 --> 01:02:51.340
Sigrid is twenty!

01:02:52.620 --> 01:02:54.782
I don't care,
I know I'm right.

01:02:55.062 --> 01:02:56.665
It doesn't interest me anymore.

01:02:56.705 --> 01:02:59.284
It spoils my memories!
It's not constructive!

01:02:59.331 --> 01:03:02.932
They'll sue and it'll go on
for months and months.

01:03:04.695 --> 01:03:06.229
They can replace me.

01:03:06.346 --> 01:03:07.422
It's too late.

01:03:07.482 --> 01:03:09.782
Klaus doesn't want
anyone else for Helena.

01:03:09.848 --> 01:03:11.291
So, I'm a hostage!

01:03:11.395 --> 01:03:13.971
You'll be appearing in
a prestigious production

01:03:14.004 --> 01:03:16.578
that's been waiting for
you for twenty years.

01:03:16.678 --> 01:03:19.081
I'm asking you
to get me out of this.

01:03:19.201 --> 01:03:22.201
Great! But, like I said,
it won't be cheap.

01:03:22.248 --> 01:03:23.994
Figure something out!

01:03:24.087 --> 01:03:26.043
There's no use getting upset.

01:03:26.123 --> 01:03:27.717
We'll take care of it.

01:03:27.803 --> 01:03:30.570
But, I'm giving you
due diligence, okay?

01:06:05.164 --> 01:06:07.450
Wait!
You have to stay with us.

01:06:07.577 --> 01:06:09.750
We're mutants.
Just like you.

01:06:09.837 --> 01:06:11.464
But, we all have doubts.

01:06:11.595 --> 01:06:13.311
Doubt about our powers.

01:06:13.424 --> 01:06:14.898
Are we worthy of them?

01:06:14.991 --> 01:06:16.811
Do we have the right to use them?

01:06:16.911 --> 01:06:18.687
After all,...

01:06:18.760 --> 01:06:20.260
what is good?

01:06:20.334 --> 01:06:21.974
And what is evil?

01:06:22.619 --> 01:06:24.998
And who are we to decide?

01:06:26.064 --> 01:06:29.117
Scarlett Witch and
Dr. Pretorius both agree.

01:06:30.037 --> 01:06:32.230
What you did was not treasonous.

01:06:32.377 --> 01:06:33.724
Forgive yourself.

01:06:34.159 --> 01:06:36.879
Don't judge your own actions so harshly.

01:06:37.931 --> 01:06:39.491
Uyh!

01:06:41.086 --> 01:06:43.370
Don't you understand?

01:06:43.823 --> 01:06:45.370
This is no mistake.

01:06:45.653 --> 01:06:49.400
I have been double-crossing
the Alliance for a very long time now.

01:06:49.549 --> 01:06:52.747
And reporting directly
to Sargon.

01:06:52.835 --> 01:06:54.213
And you know why?

01:06:56.171 --> 01:06:59.798
Because I am madly in love with him.

01:07:00.415 --> 01:07:02.942
Do you remember when
he attacked our Dohl's outpost?

01:07:03.035 --> 01:07:05.955
I tried to fight him then,
but, I was alone and I failed.

01:07:06.029 --> 01:07:07.448
You weren't there.

01:07:07.900 --> 01:07:10.747
Neither was Doctor Pretorius,
and neither was Scarlett Witch.

01:07:10.780 --> 01:07:14.153
He led me into a gravitational field
that neutralized my powers.

01:07:14.233 --> 01:07:15.573
He bolted me.

01:07:15.686 --> 01:07:17.053
We tried to find you.

01:07:17.121 --> 01:07:18.633
I woke up alone!

01:07:19.640 --> 01:07:21.874
A prisoner in his fortress.

01:07:21.952 --> 01:07:23.606
And I know that he raped you.

01:07:24.096 --> 01:07:25.116
Yes

01:07:25.187 --> 01:07:26.989
He didn't rape me.

01:07:28.423 --> 01:07:30.165
I fell in love with him.

01:07:30.211 --> 01:07:31.794
I refuse to believe.

01:07:31.843 --> 01:07:35.220
Sargon is not a mutant.
But, he understands mutants' desires.

01:07:35.281 --> 01:07:37.734
I became his lover.
It's the only reason he set me free.

01:07:37.773 --> 01:07:39.189
You are crazy.

01:07:39.383 --> 01:07:41.042
Sargon loves no-one.

01:07:41.122 --> 01:07:43.883
He used me and then
he cast me aside.

01:07:43.980 --> 01:07:47.170
But maybe if I obey him,
maybe if I follow his orders,...

01:07:48.537 --> 01:07:50.727
he might just take me back.

01:08:19.697 --> 01:08:21.777
And place your bets, please.

01:08:25.761 --> 01:08:28.335
The last bet, thank you.
No more bets.

01:08:28.381 --> 01:08:29.582
Feeling lucky.

01:08:30.801 --> 01:08:33.045
28, black.

01:08:42.376 --> 01:08:44.376
Place your bets, please.

01:08:51.366 --> 01:08:52.898
9, red.

01:08:55.962 --> 01:08:58.238
Last bets, please.
That's it.

01:08:58.294 --> 01:08:59.569
Why, I stayed because of you.

01:08:59.609 --> 01:09:03.203
But, I could feel my brain
cells dying one by one.

01:09:03.298 --> 01:09:05.443
Okay, but you don't
find her amazing?

01:09:06.260 --> 01:09:07.921
I think she's totally fascinating.

01:09:07.977 --> 01:09:10.252
It's such a stupid character, c'mon.

01:09:10.287 --> 01:09:12.569
Because it takes place on a spaceship?

01:09:13.742 --> 01:09:16.023
I know, that if it was set
on an assembly line

01:09:16.067 --> 01:09:17.910
or like a farm or something,
you'd love it.

01:09:17.937 --> 01:09:18.943
That's true.

01:09:18.970 --> 01:09:23.133
I have a hard time taking bimbos
in astronaut suits and Maliots and...

01:09:23.571 --> 01:09:25.805
generic pop psychology seriously.

01:09:25.845 --> 01:09:27.281
Been there and done that.

01:09:27.568 --> 01:09:28.591
I like it.

01:09:28.629 --> 01:09:32.037
I know... I know you do.
I'm sorry.

01:09:32.953 --> 01:09:34.831
There's no less truth...

01:09:34.890 --> 01:09:37.305
than in a more
supposedly serious film.

01:09:37.741 --> 01:09:40.520
She goes deep into
the darker side of her character.

01:09:41.371 --> 01:09:43.661
It's daring.
It's really daring.

01:09:43.894 --> 01:09:46.625
In a... in a big movie like that,
it's fucking cool.

01:09:46.881 --> 01:09:48.758
Well, she's got a great presence.

01:09:48.825 --> 01:09:51.957
But, I don't see
what's so daring about it.

01:09:53.522 --> 01:09:55.826
Despite her superpowers?

01:09:58.259 --> 01:09:59.920
Her superpowers?

01:09:59.980 --> 01:10:02.287
- Yes, her superpowers.
- Her superpowers?

01:10:02.340 --> 01:10:03.742
Yes, her superpowers.

01:10:03.795 --> 01:10:07.282
So what if it's a convention? But, it's no
dumber than any other convention.

01:10:07.615 --> 01:10:10.905
Despite her superpowers,
she's emotionally defenseless.

01:10:11.132 --> 01:10:13.015
She's in love,
but she's not loved in return.

01:10:13.059 --> 01:10:15.655
This impossible love for Sargon,
the Alliance's worst enemy,

01:10:15.688 --> 01:10:17.328
leads her to betrayal and manic...

01:10:17.389 --> 01:10:18.409
Fucking shit!

01:10:18.672 --> 01:10:21.178
Are you telling me there's nothing there,
worth playing there?

01:10:21.245 --> 01:10:23.945
I don't know, I don't know, Val.
I don't know.

01:10:27.447 --> 01:10:29.337
She knows that it means her downfall.

01:10:29.383 --> 01:10:31.895
But, that is the ultimate
truth of her desire.

01:10:31.948 --> 01:10:33.790
It's fucking powerful.

01:10:35.639 --> 01:10:39.235
Oh, my God!
I hate you sometimes so much!

01:10:39.289 --> 01:10:41.816
You're making my head spin.

01:10:42.575 --> 01:10:47.522
And Sargon,
you find him interesting, too?

01:10:49.579 --> 01:10:50.710
Yeah, I do.

01:10:50.770 --> 01:10:52.216
Oh!
Good!

01:10:55.609 --> 01:10:57.463
No, Sargon sucks.

01:10:59.688 --> 01:11:01.509
Jesus Christ!

01:11:14.700 --> 01:11:16.200
All of it?

01:11:18.161 --> 01:11:19.441
Did you see that?

01:11:19.587 --> 01:11:21.827
My magical door opening power?

01:11:21.896 --> 01:11:23.329
My door...

01:11:23.969 --> 01:11:25.809
Sure you can drive?

01:11:26.247 --> 01:11:27.892
I had the same drinks as you.

01:11:27.952 --> 01:11:29.614
That's my point.

01:11:36.658 --> 01:11:38.419
Go, go, go, go.

01:11:56.949 --> 01:11:58.126
So...

01:11:58.420 --> 01:12:01.028
what you were saying earlier,
what's that...

01:12:01.751 --> 01:12:03.182
unlike Jo-Ann,

01:12:03.256 --> 01:12:05.576
I don't take that kind
of role seriously.

01:12:05.650 --> 01:12:06.750
Huh?

01:12:06.918 --> 01:12:08.879
What?
No.

01:12:08.959 --> 01:12:11.521
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Hmm.

01:12:11.744 --> 01:12:15.433
I have disdain for
those characters and their...

01:12:16.268 --> 01:12:19.427
cartoonish psychology.
But, she doesn't.

01:12:20.076 --> 01:12:22.275
Hhh, which makes her superior to me.

01:12:22.329 --> 01:12:24.482
Oh-oh, don't get jealous

01:12:24.575 --> 01:12:26.302
It's not an attractive quality.

01:12:26.378 --> 01:12:30.105
She dives head first into
a character's ambiguities, but...

01:12:31.373 --> 01:12:32.713
I don't.

01:12:33.853 --> 01:12:35.965
That's why you admire...

01:12:36.126 --> 01:12:37.718
what she does.

01:12:38.527 --> 01:12:39.591
Yes.

01:12:40.159 --> 01:12:43.762
You know, I think that when you watch her
in a movie like the one we saw tonight,

01:12:43.822 --> 01:12:45.472
there is...

01:12:45.898 --> 01:12:47.810
there is no distance there.

01:12:47.898 --> 01:12:50.085
It's normal.
It's...

01:12:50.965 --> 01:12:52.228
Cultural, right?

01:12:52.297 --> 01:12:53.868
Yes, agreed.

01:12:54.241 --> 01:12:56.164
What's wrong with my acting?

01:12:56.238 --> 01:12:57.331
Nothing.

01:12:57.406 --> 01:13:00.891
What do I need to do
to make you admire me?

01:13:00.931 --> 01:13:02.821
Do I think too much?
Huh?

01:13:02.890 --> 01:13:04.914
Am I too classical?

01:13:05.041 --> 01:13:07.144
Am I not liberated like Jo-Ann?

01:13:07.424 --> 01:13:10.219
You're here to talk to me,
so starting talking.

01:13:10.364 --> 01:13:11.577
Hmm?

01:13:11.671 --> 01:13:13.337
I do not know,
you...

01:13:14.337 --> 01:13:17.300
you... you can't be as
accomplished as you are

01:13:17.362 --> 01:13:20.193
and as well rounded as
an actress that you are,

01:13:20.903 --> 01:13:23.003
and still expect to hold onto
the privileges of youth,

01:13:23.030 --> 01:13:24.616
it just doesn't work like that.

01:13:24.859 --> 01:13:25.987
Oh.

01:13:26.960 --> 01:13:29.073
So, I'm allowed to not be old,

01:13:29.120 --> 01:13:32.000
as long as I don't want
to be young, is that it?

01:13:32.060 --> 01:13:34.647
Yeah, I don't know.
I guess so.

01:13:35.414 --> 01:13:37.589
Yes, totally.
Well put.

01:13:41.557 --> 01:13:43.010
Fuck.

01:13:49.632 --> 01:13:51.898
I think may be a goodnight.

01:13:54.418 --> 01:13:56.374
Wait, wait, wait!

01:13:59.387 --> 01:14:02.307
You, you didn't tell me
how it went with Berndt.

01:14:04.414 --> 01:14:07.726
Yeah, well, you know,
I fuck Berndt.

01:14:08.572 --> 01:14:10.641
I thought you wouldn't
believe me anyway.

01:14:10.722 --> 01:14:11.954
Try me.

01:14:12.092 --> 01:14:14.519
Maybe you'll manage
to persuade me.

01:14:14.746 --> 01:14:16.946
I'm... exhausted.

01:14:16.986 --> 01:14:19.859
I don't know.
I don't have the energy.

01:14:20.561 --> 01:14:22.681
All right.
Goodnight.

01:14:23.901 --> 01:14:25.284
Oh, I spoke to Jay.

01:14:25.318 --> 01:14:28.764
He, he doesn't think
he can get me out of the contract.

01:14:30.804 --> 01:14:32.331
Yeah, I figured.

01:14:37.852 --> 01:14:40.712
Please knock when
you enter my office.

01:14:41.892 --> 01:14:43.315
You summoned me.

01:14:43.425 --> 01:14:46.115
I didn't summon you,
I asked you to come.

01:14:46.208 --> 01:14:47.608
What's the difference?

01:14:47.706 --> 01:14:51.751
What? The difference is when I summon you,
it's for professional reasons.

01:14:51.832 --> 01:14:54.842
When I ask you to come,
it's for personal reasons.

01:14:54.975 --> 01:14:56.875
- So, it's personal.
- Yes.

01:14:56.922 --> 01:14:58.308
All the more reason not to knock.

01:14:58.348 --> 01:15:01.224
Everyone knocks before
coming into my office.

01:15:01.604 --> 01:15:04.964
I could have been in a meeting,
or on a private call.

01:15:05.247 --> 01:15:07.957
I'm surprised that
Josephine let you through.

01:15:08.010 --> 01:15:09.814
I told Josephine
it didn't concern her.

01:15:09.855 --> 01:15:12.284
- She understood perfectly well.
- Understood what?

01:15:13.257 --> 01:15:15.147
That we have a
personal relationship.

01:15:15.257 --> 01:15:18.066
Since when does Josephine know that...

01:15:18.153 --> 01:15:21.026
we have what you call a
"personal relationship."?

01:15:21.113 --> 01:15:23.221
Not to be stupid,
she has eyes.

01:15:23.369 --> 01:15:24.689
You want me to draw a picture?

01:15:24.753 --> 01:15:26.756
Please don't draw me a picture.

01:15:27.713 --> 01:15:29.816
I thought it was
between you and me.

01:15:30.843 --> 01:15:32.409
I'm appalled.

01:15:34.018 --> 01:15:36.268
Who else knows?

01:15:37.808 --> 01:15:39.275
I don't know.

01:15:40.068 --> 01:15:42.704
But in an office,
word gets around pretty fast.

01:15:43.205 --> 01:15:45.338
You hired me as
your personal assistant.

01:15:45.384 --> 01:15:47.018
I'm under qualified.

01:15:48.620 --> 01:15:51.260
Everyone understood right away
the I could come and go as I pleased

01:15:51.294 --> 01:15:53.547
and I created a vacuum around you.

01:15:53.911 --> 01:15:55.661
To keep my hold on you.

01:15:55.733 --> 01:15:58.094
"Created a vacuum."

01:15:59.336 --> 01:16:01.261
To keep your hold.

01:16:05.707 --> 01:16:07.514
Don't you realize?

01:16:07.920 --> 01:16:09.194
No.

01:16:09.554 --> 01:16:11.427
I don't see things that way.

01:16:11.712 --> 01:16:13.927
Then everyone else got it
before you did.

01:16:30.527 --> 01:16:32.680
Shall we stop here?

01:16:33.113 --> 01:16:34.506
Sure.

01:16:38.256 --> 01:16:40.992
Can you repeat
Sigrid's last lines?

01:16:46.792 --> 01:16:49.362
Then everyone else got it
before you did.

01:16:51.137 --> 01:16:53.919
Helena pauses
and stares at Sigrid.

01:16:55.112 --> 01:16:57.532
What started at
my place that night,...

01:16:59.542 --> 01:17:01.301
I won't deny a thing.

01:17:04.119 --> 01:17:06.544
I probably wanted it,
I don't know.

01:17:08.058 --> 01:17:10.598
It's as if you put
this idea in my head.

01:17:11.017 --> 01:17:13.192
If you allowed yourself
to be manipulated,

01:17:13.245 --> 01:17:15.185
it's because you wanted it.

01:17:16.554 --> 01:17:17.791
I don't want anything.

01:17:17.851 --> 01:17:18.931
Stop!

01:17:18.986 --> 01:17:21.357
I can't stand that
condescending tone of yours!

01:17:21.410 --> 01:17:23.824
Do you want to be clear?
This can't go on!

01:17:24.208 --> 01:17:25.455
Whatever you say.

01:17:25.507 --> 01:17:27.701
It's... I, I thought it over,
it's finished.

01:17:27.795 --> 01:17:28.875
So, I'll leave.

01:17:28.928 --> 01:17:31.115
No, you'll stay.
You do your job well.

01:17:31.163 --> 01:17:32.940
I have no complaints.

01:17:34.812 --> 01:17:37.365
- I stay and it's finished?
- If we stop.

01:17:37.511 --> 01:17:39.647
- And act as if it never happened.
- Yes.

01:17:39.744 --> 01:17:42.240
Helena, you're not capable of that.

01:17:45.491 --> 01:17:48.378
If I stay, nothing will change.
You'll be my lover.

01:17:49.191 --> 01:17:51.104
- No.
- You will.

01:17:51.158 --> 01:17:53.374
And I'll keep keep driving
everyone else away.

01:17:53.847 --> 01:17:55.981
And I'll have a tighter
and tighter hold on you.

01:17:56.056 --> 01:17:57.406
- Is that what you want?
- No.

01:17:57.471 --> 01:18:00.212
Not necessarily.
I'm just telling you how it is.

01:18:00.446 --> 01:18:02.885
But if you want me to leave,
just say so.

01:18:08.766 --> 01:18:10.125
She doesn't speak.

01:18:10.212 --> 01:18:12.432
Say it.
It's time.

01:18:13.331 --> 01:18:15.304
End of Act Two.

01:18:19.834 --> 01:18:21.288
You hungry?

01:18:21.371 --> 01:18:22.458
Yep.

01:18:42.206 --> 01:18:44.870
"You'll be my lover."

01:18:47.044 --> 01:18:49.926
"I'll keep driving
everyone else away."

01:18:49.966 --> 01:18:52.755
"I'll have a tighter and
tighter hold on you."

01:18:52.802 --> 01:18:55.609
Honestly,
you don't find this ridiculous?

01:18:55.653 --> 01:18:57.255
Why?
Because she speaks brutally?

01:18:57.340 --> 01:19:00.102
No, because it's phony.
I don't believe it.

01:19:01.985 --> 01:19:04.842
So you don't think people can be
blinded by their own emotions?

01:19:04.891 --> 01:19:07.135
Yes, I do,
but not to that extent.

01:19:07.524 --> 01:19:09.910
It's too theoretical.

01:19:10.769 --> 01:19:12.603
Even a little stupid.

01:19:14.846 --> 01:19:16.169
It's theater.

01:19:16.216 --> 01:19:19.363
It's an interpretation of life
that can be truer than life itself.

01:19:20.452 --> 01:19:22.542
Sigrid puts Helena's
desires into words.

01:19:22.587 --> 01:19:26.288
She says the unspoken,
she... formulates it.

01:19:26.414 --> 01:19:27.562
Cruelly.

01:19:27.689 --> 01:19:28.712
Okay, cruelly.

01:19:28.766 --> 01:19:30.938
Yeah, cruelly,
because she's up to no good.

01:19:31.314 --> 01:19:33.438
You're not in the character's skin.
You...

01:19:33.512 --> 01:19:35.017
I have no choice.
I have to be them.

01:19:35.057 --> 01:19:36.617
I have to identify with them.

01:19:36.674 --> 01:19:40.207
When it's phony,
I feel it... viscerally.

01:19:42.452 --> 01:19:47.024
It can be uh... literary,
but still be true.

01:19:49.611 --> 01:19:52.372
I can feel the difference.
I can hear it.

01:20:39.259 --> 01:20:40.539
- Maria?
- Hhh?

01:20:40.626 --> 01:20:43.194
We gotta go.
The Sun's about to go down.

01:20:49.240 --> 01:20:51.403
I know a shortcut
a little further up.

01:20:51.456 --> 01:20:52.817
But, it's steep.
But, uh...

01:20:52.873 --> 01:20:55.449
it'll take us straight to Val Fex.

01:20:56.119 --> 01:20:59.152
- I htought Val Fex is that way.
- No.

01:21:03.424 --> 01:21:05.652
Are you sure this is
the right path, huh?

01:21:05.706 --> 01:21:06.919
Uh...

01:21:07.025 --> 01:21:09.012
Actually, not really.

01:21:09.187 --> 01:21:11.123
I'm not even sure
it's a path.

01:21:11.230 --> 01:21:14.846
Well, we might have pooped-up somewhere.
I don't know.

01:21:15.317 --> 01:21:17.210
I think you're right.

01:21:18.777 --> 01:21:21.163
I'm pretty sure Val Fex is um...

01:21:21.811 --> 01:21:23.540
not this way.

01:21:25.914 --> 01:21:28.825
Anyway, we're heading down,
we'll wind up somewhere.

01:21:31.285 --> 01:21:33.965
I think this road
takes us to Maloja.

01:21:36.101 --> 01:21:38.514
What'll we do when
we get to Maloja?

01:21:39.438 --> 01:21:41.035
We'll take a bus.

01:21:45.995 --> 01:21:50.018
You know, you don't have to keep me on
if you find my ideas simplistic.

01:21:52.023 --> 01:21:53.718
What makes you say that?

01:21:54.685 --> 01:21:57.019
If you find my point of view...

01:21:57.858 --> 01:21:59.754
uninteresting.
I...

01:22:01.433 --> 01:22:04.327
Ah, I don't really know
what I'm doing here. I...

01:22:05.621 --> 01:22:08.028
I can run lines with you,
but I don't really see the point,

01:22:08.061 --> 01:22:09.355
you can find anyone to do that.

01:22:09.401 --> 01:22:13.217
No, all I'm saying is that thinking
about a text is different from living it.

01:22:13.250 --> 01:22:15.103
It's not against you.

01:22:15.344 --> 01:22:16.784
You...

01:22:17.314 --> 01:22:19.494
You hate the play
and you hate her.

01:22:22.946 --> 01:22:24.886
You don't have
to take it out on me.

01:22:25.266 --> 01:22:27.193
I'm just doing my job.

01:22:41.589 --> 01:22:43.110
Ready?

01:22:44.030 --> 01:22:45.770
- You ready?
- Yes.

01:22:52.873 --> 01:22:54.486
Don't lie to me!

01:22:54.625 --> 01:22:58.779
You received a confirmation
for a flight to Tokyo!

01:22:58.839 --> 01:23:00.646
You're reading my mails now?

01:23:00.700 --> 01:23:01.943
Aren't you ashamed?

01:23:01.984 --> 01:23:04.040
I haven't felt shame in a long time.

01:23:04.074 --> 01:23:06.172
I went through all your desk drawers,
your notebooks,

01:23:06.205 --> 01:23:08.574
and I'm doing it because
you want to leave me.

01:23:08.660 --> 01:23:10.660
Now I know when and how.

01:23:10.794 --> 01:23:14.265
Helena is restless,
Sigrid remains poised.

01:23:14.683 --> 01:23:16.385
All you had to do was ask.

01:23:16.472 --> 01:23:19.123
Yes, I accepted a job in Tokyo.

01:23:19.222 --> 01:23:20.808
A pharmaceutical lab.

01:23:20.921 --> 01:23:23.315
I think it'll be much more interesting
than the work I'm doing here.

01:23:23.355 --> 01:23:25.915
More interesting than
what you're doing here?

01:23:26.135 --> 01:23:28.135
Ha... Haven't I given...

01:23:28.200 --> 01:23:29.842
in to every demand you've made?

01:23:29.883 --> 01:23:33.888
No other company would have given you
that kind of responsibility, and power!

01:23:33.935 --> 01:23:35.571
Exactly.

01:23:35.852 --> 01:23:37.792
It's weighing on me.

01:23:38.344 --> 01:23:40.318
I know this place in and out.

01:23:40.401 --> 01:23:42.022
The world moves.

01:23:42.242 --> 01:23:44.775
I wanna feel that.
I wanna be part of it.

01:23:45.247 --> 01:23:48.036
I want to travel.
Switzerland is too provincial.

01:24:01.484 --> 01:24:04.224
She takes a deep breath
and regains her composure.

01:24:04.299 --> 01:24:06.764
And with me you don't feel free?

01:24:07.090 --> 01:24:09.376
You've become too
dependent on me.

01:24:09.743 --> 01:24:11.216
It's unhealthy.

01:24:11.403 --> 01:24:12.610
And what do I get in return?

01:24:12.661 --> 01:24:15.142
I give you whatever you want,
you know that!

01:24:15.183 --> 01:24:16.430
Oh.

01:24:16.497 --> 01:24:20.233
Like a job at a dead-end company
that's about to go down the drain?

01:24:20.285 --> 01:24:22.479
How can you say
a thing like that?

01:24:22.527 --> 01:24:24.785
Open your eyes!
My poor Helena.

01:24:24.831 --> 01:24:26.447
I'm not your poor Helena!

01:24:26.494 --> 01:24:28.087
Nothing I've learned here
is of any use to me.

01:24:28.122 --> 01:24:30.381
I'm not your poor Helena!

01:24:31.194 --> 01:24:32.867
It never lasts.

01:24:33.175 --> 01:24:35.841
You should listen to what
the bankers are telling you.

01:24:35.934 --> 01:24:37.195
And your board members.

01:24:37.241 --> 01:24:39.355
That's not true!

01:24:41.754 --> 01:24:45.827
God! This relationship with this...
between these women...

01:24:46.760 --> 01:24:47.895
is disturbing.

01:24:48.009 --> 01:24:49.320
is disturbing.

01:24:49.553 --> 01:24:51.600
Nowadays, people say
"disturbing" about everything,

01:24:51.640 --> 01:24:54.546
even the most conventional ideas.

01:24:55.092 --> 01:24:57.470
It's a...
it's a male fantasy.

01:24:57.542 --> 01:24:59.423
Ah, no.
It's not.

01:24:59.728 --> 01:25:02.744
I don't know why I should be
helping to bring her to life.

01:25:02.801 --> 01:25:05.668
I thought you weren't saying stuff
like this when you're playing Sigrid.

01:25:05.721 --> 01:25:07.981
Well, I was a kid when
I was playing Sigrid.

01:25:08.434 --> 01:25:11.325
I, I wasn't asking
those kind of questions.

01:25:11.608 --> 01:25:13.545
Like Jo-Ann in her science fiction film?

01:25:13.605 --> 01:25:15.418
Yeah, probably.

01:25:17.367 --> 01:25:19.624
Well, don't you want to get
that innocence back?

01:25:19.812 --> 01:25:21.854
You can't get innocent twice.

01:25:21.926 --> 01:25:23.146
You can.

01:25:23.455 --> 01:25:26.327
If you just accepted Helena
the way you accepted Sigrid.

01:25:26.371 --> 01:25:29.707
Obviously it's easier to relate
to strength rather than weakness.

01:25:29.928 --> 01:25:31.904
Youth is better than maturity.

01:25:32.267 --> 01:25:35.551
Cruelty is cool.
Suffering sucks.

01:25:36.897 --> 01:25:38.319
She...

01:25:38.553 --> 01:25:41.280
She's mature and she's innocent.

01:25:41.571 --> 01:25:44.773
She's innocent in her own right,
that's what I like about her.

01:25:49.864 --> 01:25:52.310
I'll make some coffee.
You want some?

01:25:54.431 --> 01:25:57.287
Cruelty is cool and
suffering sucks.

01:26:15.445 --> 01:26:17.361
You didn't answer me.

01:26:18.330 --> 01:26:20.482
You have your interpretation of the play.

01:26:20.727 --> 01:26:23.055
I think mine is just confusing you.

01:26:23.720 --> 01:26:25.446
It's frustrating me.

01:26:26.489 --> 01:26:28.006
It's uncomfortable.

01:26:28.366 --> 01:26:29.846
Not good.

01:26:38.108 --> 01:26:39.411
Stay.

01:26:43.468 --> 01:26:44.951
No, no.

01:26:45.230 --> 01:26:47.112
Please, stay.

01:26:48.627 --> 01:26:50.200
I need you.

01:28:31.291 --> 01:28:32.438
Thank you.

01:28:32.546 --> 01:28:35.255
I prefer 18th century
music to any other.

01:28:35.274 --> 01:28:37.672
It's so bright and lively.

01:28:38.170 --> 01:28:39.190
Yes, me too.

01:28:39.251 --> 01:28:41.890
Romantic music's so sad
and depressing.

01:28:42.379 --> 01:28:45.019
But, I'd rather listen to rock music
any day of the week, though.

01:28:45.072 --> 01:28:46.785
- Even the worse.
- Not me.

01:28:46.872 --> 01:28:49.232
I've had too much of it,
I'm sick of it.

01:28:49.305 --> 01:28:51.645
Oh, you're such a snob!

01:28:51.856 --> 01:28:54.128
No, tastes can get worn out.

01:28:54.191 --> 01:28:56.281
Kinda like desire.

01:28:57.387 --> 01:29:00.507
I've never listened to Handel properly.
I think he's excellent.

01:29:00.707 --> 01:29:03.530
I haven't been this moved
by music in ages.

01:29:05.057 --> 01:29:06.743
You're making fun of me.

01:29:06.856 --> 01:29:09.076
I'm not.
But, I just...

01:29:10.446 --> 01:29:13.888
I find it really cute that you're
trying to put up with my ideas.

01:29:14.118 --> 01:29:16.118
You know I'm not a music whiz.

01:29:16.209 --> 01:29:19.128
I mean, besides that my family
practically spoon fed me

01:29:19.154 --> 01:29:20.921
which is incredibly specialized

01:29:20.961 --> 01:29:23.857
I don't know a thing about music.

01:29:25.728 --> 01:29:27.224
Thank you.

01:29:27.866 --> 01:29:28.895
So...

01:29:28.944 --> 01:29:30.601
How did it go with your wife?

01:29:30.688 --> 01:29:32.211
Very well.

01:29:32.455 --> 01:29:34.675
No, I'm kidding.
It was horrible.

01:29:34.996 --> 01:29:36.820
But you know, she...

01:29:36.887 --> 01:29:39.107
she's not the type
to wear her heart on her sleeve.

01:29:39.167 --> 01:29:41.367
I think she was expecting it.

01:29:41.487 --> 01:29:42.721
Did you tell her about me?

01:29:42.767 --> 01:29:44.554
No, I said, you know,...

01:29:44.595 --> 01:29:47.727
I'd be going off on my own
to write my book and wouldn't be back.

01:29:47.788 --> 01:29:49.605
Then she must be
suspecting something.

01:29:49.644 --> 01:29:51.517
She has no idea
you and I know each other.

01:29:51.564 --> 01:29:54.197
Well, she will.
I mean, when it hits the tabloids.

01:29:54.470 --> 01:29:56.037
They're not gonna find us here.

01:29:56.077 --> 01:29:58.967
They can find us anywhere.
It's their job, you know.

01:29:59.540 --> 01:30:01.387
Did you say anything
to Maria Enders?

01:30:01.433 --> 01:30:03.610
Just that I'll be taking
advantage of my press tour

01:30:03.664 --> 01:30:05.124
and come and say "Hi" to her.

01:30:05.160 --> 01:30:06.954
She didn't find that strange?

01:30:07.020 --> 01:30:08.299
I talked to her assistant,

01:30:08.345 --> 01:30:11.412
nd she didn't seem to question it.
So, I guess not.

01:30:26.668 --> 01:30:29.061
Hey, she's over there.

01:30:29.128 --> 01:30:30.448
- Hi.
- Hi!

01:30:30.473 --> 01:30:31.208
Hi.

01:30:31.241 --> 01:30:33.375
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you too.

01:30:33.626 --> 01:30:35.337
- Wow!
- What?

01:30:35.389 --> 01:30:37.551
I never would have recognized you.

01:30:37.604 --> 01:30:38.620
- Really?
- Hhh.

01:30:38.647 --> 01:30:40.867
Well, I mean, if you've only seen me
on the internet or in a movie,

01:30:40.901 --> 01:30:43.674
- that's not really a big surprise.
- I apologize, it's a little weird.

01:30:43.731 --> 01:30:46.461
Well, you, on the other hand,
look exactly like all your roles.

01:30:46.828 --> 01:30:49.014
I hope not all of them.

01:30:49.070 --> 01:30:51.371
No, no, no.
Only the better ones.

01:30:51.761 --> 01:30:54.538
Rest assured that
you don't look like Nemesis.

01:30:55.351 --> 01:30:57.197
This is Chris.
He's a... he's a novelist.

01:30:57.244 --> 01:30:58.857
- Hi.
- Hi. Nice to meet you, Chris.

01:30:58.904 --> 01:31:00.214
- My assistant, Kate.
- Hi.

01:31:00.247 --> 01:31:02.527
It's, it's so good to meet
the both of you, seriously.

01:31:02.594 --> 01:31:03.734
Yeah.

01:31:04.060 --> 01:31:05.080
Hello!

01:31:05.127 --> 01:31:06.908
May I get you
anything to drink?

01:31:07.001 --> 01:31:08.803
- A cognac for me, please.
- Yeah.

01:31:08.903 --> 01:31:10.696
- I'll have the same.
- Okay.

01:31:10.736 --> 01:31:12.550
- I'm fine, thanks.
- All right.

01:31:12.583 --> 01:31:14.440
What herbal teas do you have?

01:31:14.520 --> 01:31:17.527
We have verbena,
mint and chamomile.

01:31:17.596 --> 01:31:18.830
I'll take chamomile, please.

01:31:18.863 --> 01:31:20.607
- Yeah, sure.
- Thank you.

01:31:23.176 --> 01:31:27.470
I don't think you understand
how much of an honor this is for me.

01:31:27.574 --> 01:31:29.792
When I was 15,
I saw um...

01:31:30.025 --> 01:31:33.355
Oh, my God, the movie you did,
with the CIA and Harrison Ford.

01:31:33.461 --> 01:31:36.161
- I'm so sorry, I'm blanking out.
- "A Beetle on its Back"

01:31:36.201 --> 01:31:38.283
"A Beetle on its Back"
with Harrison Ford.

01:31:38.329 --> 01:31:39.797
You blew my mind.

01:31:39.847 --> 01:31:41.491
You, you...

01:31:41.849 --> 01:31:43.407
You were the epitome of class.

01:31:43.495 --> 01:31:46.045
You were everything
I ever wanted to be as an actress.

01:31:46.133 --> 01:31:48.345
And I mean the way that
you battled those politicians

01:31:48.385 --> 01:31:51.518
and then the military brass men,
it was, it was captivating.

01:31:51.564 --> 01:31:54.626
It was my first Hollywood film
I was in, and the last.

01:31:54.975 --> 01:31:56.322
Um...

01:31:56.651 --> 01:31:58.384
Sydney Pollack was really nice.

01:31:58.418 --> 01:32:00.678
But, sometimes I didn't understand
what he was saying,

01:32:00.718 --> 01:32:02.351
so I was too shy to ask.

01:32:02.443 --> 01:32:05.785
But fortunately,
Harrison was there to help.

01:32:05.903 --> 01:32:07.225
A lot.

01:32:09.193 --> 01:32:12.003
Well, then, of course,
after that I... I begged

01:32:12.056 --> 01:32:15.300
my parents to let me see you on stage,
and the "The Seagull". And...

01:32:15.399 --> 01:32:18.272
They didn't know who you were
before then because...

01:32:18.390 --> 01:32:20.125
well, they kinda hate movies.

01:32:20.325 --> 01:32:22.231
Well, I hope they tolerate the theater.

01:32:22.281 --> 01:32:23.334
No, no.

01:32:23.374 --> 01:32:24.814
They don't just tolerate the theatre,

01:32:24.854 --> 01:32:26.534
I mean, they, they're
absolutely in love with it.

01:32:26.574 --> 01:32:28.371
In fact, they see everything in.
And...

01:32:28.464 --> 01:32:31.424
And... um, you know,
when they saw your performance,

01:32:31.464 --> 01:32:33.891
they said it was the best Nina
they'd ever seen.

01:32:34.343 --> 01:32:36.292
And that meant a lot to me.

01:32:36.526 --> 01:32:38.729
Because that's uh, you know,
before that I...

01:32:38.856 --> 01:32:41.402
I'd never been able to tell them
that I wanted to be an actress.

01:32:41.442 --> 01:32:42.689
But, because of you...

01:32:42.786 --> 01:32:44.859
I can pursue my vocation.

01:32:45.018 --> 01:32:47.352
I, I prefer your early French films.

01:32:47.385 --> 01:32:49.598
There was, there was a cycle
at the ICA in London.

01:32:49.651 --> 01:32:51.642
- Uh-huh.
- I, I saw almost all of them.

01:32:51.683 --> 01:32:52.903
And you came.

01:32:52.937 --> 01:32:54.386
You, you probably
don't remember.

01:32:54.433 --> 01:32:56.893
Oh, I remember it perfectly well.

01:32:56.986 --> 01:33:00.803
I was fascinated by how freely
you spoke about your work.

01:33:00.838 --> 01:33:03.581
And um uh
someone asked you um...

01:33:03.694 --> 01:33:06.468
if you had any regrets,
and you said...

01:33:06.574 --> 01:33:08.390
"We're not allowed to regret anything.

01:33:08.450 --> 01:33:09.590
If we're sincere,

01:33:09.630 --> 01:33:11.997
then we're the sum total
of our experiences,

01:33:12.030 --> 01:33:13.570
with no exceptions."

01:33:13.998 --> 01:33:15.245
I said that?

01:33:15.309 --> 01:33:17.382
Well, not word for word.
Something like that.

01:33:17.432 --> 01:33:19.232
And you don't think that anymore?

01:33:19.285 --> 01:33:21.152
Oh, uh...
No. Um...

01:33:21.307 --> 01:33:26.763
I... I completely agree with that,
one hundred percent.

01:33:28.872 --> 01:33:32.465
You know, I am, I'm incredibly
intimidated to take on your role.

01:33:32.552 --> 01:33:35.332
I mean, no-one's gonna be able
to do it like you did, and...

01:33:35.405 --> 01:33:37.301
I hope you don't
judge me too harshly.

01:33:37.407 --> 01:33:39.828
Um, we'll all have our own way
into a character.

01:33:39.861 --> 01:33:41.001
They're all good.

01:33:41.060 --> 01:33:43.474
Well, I cannot wait to do
the re-do tomorrow.

01:33:43.516 --> 01:33:46.262
We are working at Wilhelm's chalet,
I hope that's okay with you?

01:33:46.302 --> 01:33:47.302
Yeah, sure.

01:33:47.342 --> 01:33:50.392
As long as his ghost isn't
watching over us the entire time.

01:33:50.438 --> 01:33:51.765
I can't promise you that.

01:33:51.812 --> 01:33:53.899
But don't worry,
he's a well-meaning ghost.

01:33:53.991 --> 01:33:55.435
Oh, "Well meaning".

01:33:55.781 --> 01:33:57.068
I don't know about that.

01:33:57.115 --> 01:33:58.501
Nor do I.

01:34:00.294 --> 01:34:04.695
You know, it's incredibly brave of you
to take on the role of Helena.

01:34:05.009 --> 01:34:08.596
It's...
it's her way of dealing with time.

01:34:08.780 --> 01:34:12.013
Yeah, it was.
I don't know, sometimes I...

01:34:13.430 --> 01:34:15.983
I tell myself that it's just a job.

01:34:16.030 --> 01:34:19.786
And I'll be happy
to move on when it's over.

01:34:20.206 --> 01:34:21.577
Hey.

01:34:22.308 --> 01:34:23.314
Thank you.

01:34:23.351 --> 01:34:25.824
You still want to see the "Snake",
you asked me the other day?

01:34:25.864 --> 01:34:26.978
Oh, yeah.

01:34:27.024 --> 01:34:29.784
The weather they're predicting
for tomorrow seems ideal.

01:34:29.823 --> 01:34:32.403
So, you better make sure
you're out there at daybreak.

01:34:32.451 --> 01:34:35.382
It's wonderful to see it
coming over the Maloja Pass.

01:34:35.456 --> 01:34:37.249
Great! Awesome!
That's amazing.

01:34:37.325 --> 01:34:38.682
- Thank you!
- Yep.

01:34:40.170 --> 01:34:42.805
I thought they were really nice.

01:34:43.958 --> 01:34:45.451
Yeah, it's true!
I, I...

01:34:45.506 --> 01:34:48.992
She's a lot more interesting
than the person you described.

01:34:49.232 --> 01:34:50.939
I didn't know
her parents were musicians,

01:34:50.972 --> 01:34:53.666
and I liked them too.
It's...

01:34:56.258 --> 01:34:59.191
What's so funny?
Did I say something funny?

01:35:00.013 --> 01:35:02.786
They spent the whole
evening flattering you,

01:35:03.019 --> 01:35:04.479
of course, you liked them.

01:35:04.559 --> 01:35:06.032
That has nothing to do with it.

01:35:06.085 --> 01:35:08.048
No, no.
Of course not.

01:35:18.740 --> 01:35:20.480
Repeat that!

01:35:22.024 --> 01:35:23.373
What?

01:35:24.723 --> 01:35:27.397
What was that movie?
"A Beetle on its back.".

01:35:30.220 --> 01:35:32.548
I can't believe
we got the scoop tonight!

01:35:32.585 --> 01:35:33.875
What scoop?

01:35:33.921 --> 01:35:36.355
She's with Christopher Giles.

01:35:36.401 --> 01:35:38.898
Chris? His name is
Christopher Giles?

01:35:39.018 --> 01:35:41.145
- Yes.
- Is he famous?

01:35:41.311 --> 01:35:44.358
He's...
Ã¼ber famous.

01:35:44.929 --> 01:35:47.905
I can't remember which major
book prize he won, but...

01:35:49.467 --> 01:35:50.867
he's married.

01:35:50.914 --> 01:35:53.867
He's with Dorothea Von Duisburg.
The German artist?

01:35:54.280 --> 01:35:56.754
Should've showed
the serpentine monster.

01:36:00.167 --> 01:36:02.484
Never heard of neither of them!!

01:36:02.604 --> 01:36:03.937
Who?

01:36:04.717 --> 01:36:07.017
I mean, you should Google him.

01:36:07.134 --> 01:36:09.154
How do you spell his name?

01:36:09.368 --> 01:36:10.675
Giles.

01:36:10.730 --> 01:36:12.101
G-I-L-E-S.

01:36:12.156 --> 01:36:14.569
Well, he's obviously with her.

01:36:16.183 --> 01:36:17.316
Yeah!

01:36:17.436 --> 01:36:19.496
When word gets out,
it's gonna be,...

01:36:19.530 --> 01:36:21.456
like,...
a tsunami.

01:36:23.380 --> 01:36:25.393
Oh, yeah.
On their planet.

01:36:25.447 --> 01:36:27.287
Their planet has a name.

01:36:27.760 --> 01:36:29.687
It's called the "real world."

01:36:29.775 --> 01:36:31.052
Welcome!

01:36:32.844 --> 01:36:34.147
Careful with that.

01:36:34.194 --> 01:36:35.634
Come here.
Give that here to me.

01:36:35.721 --> 01:36:36.927
Stop fighting!

01:36:37.235 --> 01:36:38.362
Here.

01:36:54.722 --> 01:36:58.032
I spent all night thinking
about Helena's death.

01:36:58.451 --> 01:36:59.738
Her death?

01:37:00.072 --> 01:37:01.542
She doesn't necessarily die.

01:37:01.595 --> 01:37:03.961
She just...
She disappears.

01:37:04.122 --> 01:37:05.988
That's your interpretation.

01:37:06.071 --> 01:37:08.745
Well, it's...
it's pretty ambiguous.

01:37:09.264 --> 01:37:11.777
She goes out for a hike
and never comes back,

01:37:11.817 --> 01:37:13.737
seems clear enough to me.

01:37:14.534 --> 01:37:16.183
You don't know that.

01:37:16.255 --> 01:37:18.391
She could reinvent herself
somewhere else.

01:37:18.458 --> 01:37:19.937
There's really no way of knowing.

01:37:19.983 --> 01:37:21.928
You know, you can imagine
whatever you want.

01:37:21.995 --> 01:37:23.862
Are we going the right way?

01:37:23.995 --> 01:37:26.476
I mean, I don't mind waking up
at the crack of dawn,

01:37:26.516 --> 01:37:29.135
but not to get lost in
the mountains and miss the "Snake"!

01:37:29.229 --> 01:37:31.889
Well, we're basically here.
You happy?

01:37:32.025 --> 01:37:34.134
What makes you think we're here?

01:37:34.788 --> 01:37:37.100
I've got a map!
You want me to show you?

01:37:37.160 --> 01:37:38.433
Come here.

01:37:40.503 --> 01:37:43.699
This is the bend we just went around.
Ten minutes ago?

01:37:43.766 --> 01:37:45.751
And just around there
is the view of the valley.

01:37:45.799 --> 01:37:47.958
- See that?
- How do you know?

01:37:48.190 --> 01:37:49.472
How do...?

01:37:52.000 --> 01:37:54.695
Pain in the ass!
Jesus Christ!

01:37:55.211 --> 01:37:57.996
I don't know why you're so dead-set
on making this play say

01:37:58.036 --> 01:38:00.656
the opposite of what
it was meant to say.

01:38:00.932 --> 01:38:02.106
At twenty,...

01:38:02.967 --> 01:38:05.880
you saw Sigrid's ambition
and you saw her violence

01:38:05.926 --> 01:38:07.673
because you felt it in yourself.

01:38:07.718 --> 01:38:08.726
So?

01:38:08.835 --> 01:38:12.061
So, what I'm saying is...
the text is like an object.

01:38:12.753 --> 01:38:15.900
It's gonna change perspective
based on where you're standing.

01:38:16.560 --> 01:38:18.000
I don't know...

01:38:20.242 --> 01:38:22.036
We should go.
we're gonna miss the "Snake".

01:38:22.090 --> 01:38:23.689
Won't be any "Snake".

01:38:24.934 --> 01:38:26.268
Ah, fuck it.

01:38:26.402 --> 01:38:27.766
Whatever.

01:39:18.153 --> 01:39:19.586
Look there!

01:39:20.942 --> 01:39:22.986
Is that the "Snake"?

01:39:25.041 --> 01:39:26.257
No.

01:39:27.391 --> 01:39:29.327
No, it's just mist.

01:39:29.931 --> 01:39:31.464
Oh, fuck.

01:39:32.234 --> 01:39:33.951
When it breaks up.

01:39:36.788 --> 01:39:39.239
It's still pretty beautiful though.

01:39:39.568 --> 01:39:43.298
It's like it's gathering and
pouring out into the valley.

01:39:45.312 --> 01:39:47.855
Or maybe it is the "Snake".

01:39:49.556 --> 01:39:51.273
We have to be patient.

01:39:53.860 --> 01:39:56.426
No, it's not the "Snake".
It...

01:39:56.726 --> 01:39:58.255
Oh, yes!

01:39:58.913 --> 01:40:01.681
I think it's turning into the "Snake"!

01:40:02.140 --> 01:40:03.679
How about you?

01:40:04.951 --> 01:40:06.039
Val?

01:40:08.099 --> 01:40:10.186
What the hell are you doing?

01:40:12.405 --> 01:40:13.704
Val?

01:40:16.055 --> 01:40:17.450
Val!

01:40:18.525 --> 01:40:19.691
Val!

01:40:21.854 --> 01:40:23.076
Val!

01:40:27.255 --> 01:40:28.631
Val!

01:40:29.448 --> 01:40:31.464
Answer me!

01:40:33.449 --> 01:40:35.092
Val!

01:40:38.915 --> 01:40:40.219
Val!

01:41:53.035 --> 01:41:57.451
EPILOGUE
LONDON, A FEW WEEKS LATER

01:42:03.402 --> 01:42:05.156
How's the hotel?

01:42:05.387 --> 01:42:08.643
The hotel's fine.
Oh, thanks for the flowers.

01:42:08.695 --> 01:42:12.447
So, did you reach Klaus?
He was really impatient to see you.

01:42:12.494 --> 01:42:15.267
You have to return his calls, you know?
He thinks you're avoiding him.

01:42:15.296 --> 01:42:17.975
We're having dinner.
He's a half hour late.

01:42:18.203 --> 01:42:20.732
Oh, so, you called me to kill time.

01:42:20.907 --> 01:42:22.316
Just kidding.

01:42:22.627 --> 01:42:24.537
I'm not avoiding him.
I...

01:42:24.639 --> 01:42:26.219
I want to talk to him one-on-one.

01:42:26.274 --> 01:42:28.597
You know how reluctant I was.
I'm over that now.

01:42:28.652 --> 01:42:31.592
You know, Klaus understands
the risks you're taking.

01:42:31.634 --> 01:42:32.977
I know he's sincere.

01:42:33.021 --> 01:42:35.692
He's doing this for you
and for Wilhelm's memory.

01:42:35.739 --> 01:42:37.318
And for the publicity.

01:42:37.489 --> 01:42:40.068
Twenty years after being Sigrid,
I'm Helena.

01:42:40.122 --> 01:42:42.529
That's all the press is talking about.

01:42:42.829 --> 01:42:45.808
You know, he's like every artist of
his generation.

01:42:45.862 --> 01:42:47.815
He has a flair for P.R.

01:42:47.846 --> 01:42:49.206
Oh, and is that a crime?

01:42:49.232 --> 01:42:54.011
"To excel and to know how to show it
is to excel twice."

01:42:54.351 --> 01:42:56.444
Baltasar Gracian said that.

01:42:56.539 --> 01:42:58.952
I have no idea who that is.

01:42:59.021 --> 01:43:00.300
But, he was right.

01:43:00.340 --> 01:43:03.071
The press is talking
about you and your work.

01:43:03.130 --> 01:43:05.083
Oh, I said "OK" to pictures,
knowing of you.

01:43:05.123 --> 01:43:06.683
It is too soon, too fragile.

01:43:06.733 --> 01:43:07.897
Hold on!

01:43:09.330 --> 01:43:10.530
Yes?

01:43:12.086 --> 01:43:14.106
Uh, tell him I'm on my way down.

01:43:14.318 --> 01:43:15.526
Thank you.

01:43:17.199 --> 01:43:18.470
It's Klaus.

01:43:19.183 --> 01:43:20.570
You'll be fine.

01:43:23.798 --> 01:43:24.938
Hi.

01:43:25.765 --> 01:43:26.972
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:43:27.017 --> 01:43:29.824
Excuse me, I'm late.
But, something terrible has happened.

01:43:30.886 --> 01:43:33.754
Dorothea tried to commit suicide.
She's in a coma.

01:43:33.796 --> 01:43:34.844
Dorothea?

01:43:34.904 --> 01:43:36.747
Christopher Giles' wife.

01:43:37.676 --> 01:43:40.881
Chris, uh, Jo-Ann's friend,
you mean?

01:43:41.108 --> 01:43:43.751
Yes, but you're not supposed
to know he's Jo-Ann's friend.

01:43:43.790 --> 01:43:45.911
Well, they were together in Sils.
So...

01:43:45.986 --> 01:43:47.911
I thought it was more
recent than that...

01:43:48.038 --> 01:43:49.991
Excuse me, sir.
We can go.

01:43:50.394 --> 01:43:53.665
Well, she slit her wrists
in the studio.

01:43:54.032 --> 01:43:57.012
The housekeeper found her
in a pool of her own blood.

01:43:57.111 --> 01:43:58.779
Oh, that's awful.

01:44:00.326 --> 01:44:02.119
She's a well known artist, right?

01:44:02.243 --> 01:44:04.093
Dorothea's an amazing girl.

01:44:04.346 --> 01:44:07.687
Beautiful, talented,
everything going for her.

01:44:08.511 --> 01:44:10.191
I love her work.

01:44:10.538 --> 01:44:12.385
I don't understand.

01:44:12.987 --> 01:44:14.854
Jo-Ann is devastated.

01:44:14.927 --> 01:44:17.000
She was at an exhibition.

01:44:17.391 --> 01:44:21.911
She can't go back to the hotel.
The paparazzi have surrounded the place.

01:44:22.684 --> 01:44:25.250
I suggested she join us.
You don't mind?

01:44:25.378 --> 01:44:26.950
No, of course not.

01:44:59.507 --> 01:45:03.023
It's still just a rumor,
but the press knew something was up.

01:45:03.563 --> 01:45:06.613
Someone posted in her blog that
it was the real reason

01:45:06.659 --> 01:45:08.973
that Jo-Ann had accepted
to do a play in London.

01:45:09.033 --> 01:45:10.392
And is that true?

01:45:10.446 --> 01:45:12.283
She doesn't need a pretext
to act in London,

01:45:12.329 --> 01:45:14.776
but the paparazzi will never let go.

01:45:14.866 --> 01:45:18.622
They need her picture with Christopher.
And they're going wild.

01:45:23.750 --> 01:45:26.530
She's in her car.
She'll be here in five minutes.

01:45:29.866 --> 01:45:31.293
You wanted to talk to me?

01:45:31.340 --> 01:45:33.193
I'm sorry, I'm confused.

01:45:34.553 --> 01:45:37.341
I had a long conversation
with Rose last night.

01:45:37.413 --> 01:45:40.057
I told her that we were in London
that we were about...

01:45:40.237 --> 01:45:41.917
to start rehearsals.

01:45:42.081 --> 01:45:43.649
That made her happy, I think.

01:45:43.726 --> 01:45:47.024
I know. Now all we have to do is
not disappoint you.

01:45:48.936 --> 01:45:52.643
On thos tray, Chateau Laroze.
Thank you.

01:45:53.461 --> 01:45:57.284
Rosa gave me fragments from
Wilhelm's follow-up to "Maloja's Snake".

01:45:57.374 --> 01:45:59.027
A sign of her trust.

01:45:59.456 --> 01:46:02.996
Some of the pages make
no sense out of context, but...

01:46:03.070 --> 01:46:06.210
there are a few others that
put the play in a new light.

01:46:06.384 --> 01:46:08.998
How old was Wilhelm
when he wrote "Maloja's Snake."?

01:46:09.075 --> 01:46:10.648
Thirty-five or so?

01:46:11.036 --> 01:46:13.392
- Hmmm... 38.
-38?!

01:46:13.432 --> 01:46:15.373
Yeah, a little older
when he made the film.

01:46:15.414 --> 01:46:17.973
Well, he was still a young man,
all action.

01:46:19.403 --> 01:46:22.264
Twenty-five years later,
obviously, he was more analytical,

01:46:22.295 --> 01:46:24.184
trying to put the things in perspective,

01:46:24.218 --> 01:46:27.152
maybe, thinking about posterity.
Who knows?

01:46:27.678 --> 01:46:30.945
Isn't it better to stay faithful
to his youthful energy?

01:46:31.134 --> 01:46:33.720
- And forget the new scenes?
- Yes.

01:46:35.247 --> 01:46:37.760
Wilhelm never had any
distance or maturity.

01:46:37.808 --> 01:46:41.118
On the contrary,
his last texts got bolder and bolder,

01:46:41.172 --> 01:46:43.878
and more and more...
enigmatic.

01:46:44.834 --> 01:46:46.942
Here's another way
of looking at it.

01:46:47.671 --> 01:46:49.234
We think like him.

01:46:49.541 --> 01:46:52.511
We, we project ourselves
into the future,

01:46:52.557 --> 01:46:54.684
instead of freezing ourselves in the past

01:46:54.760 --> 01:46:56.993
Or if we...
Jo-Ann!

01:46:57.254 --> 01:46:58.540
Hey.

01:46:58.643 --> 01:46:59.908
What's happening?

01:46:59.995 --> 01:47:01.481
She's hanging on by a thread.

01:47:01.554 --> 01:47:03.401
She's lost a lot of blood,
but, uh...

01:47:03.496 --> 01:47:05.139
the doctors won't tell us anything.

01:47:05.164 --> 01:47:07.492
I mean, Chris said she was
really relaxed when he told her.

01:47:07.526 --> 01:47:09.402
She was just getting used to
the new situation.

01:47:09.438 --> 01:47:10.978
Where is Christopher?

01:47:11.346 --> 01:47:13.318
Dorothea's family
got in from Germany.

01:47:13.382 --> 01:47:15.414
And so he... he told them
to leave the hospital.

01:47:15.455 --> 01:47:17.080
So they're gonna come join us.

01:47:17.131 --> 01:47:19.251
Here?
But, that's ridiculous.

01:47:19.298 --> 01:47:22.091
He will have all the paparazzi
from the hospital on his trail.

01:47:22.136 --> 01:47:24.203
No, he said there were no paparazzi.
He'd know.

01:47:24.230 --> 01:47:26.679
He's being naive.
Of course, they are tailing him.

01:47:26.840 --> 01:47:30.633
They are just doing it discreetly.
Tell him absolutely not to join us.

01:47:36.181 --> 01:47:37.481
Come on, Chris.

01:47:37.534 --> 01:47:40.334
His voicemail's turned off.
I'll just text him.

01:47:40.801 --> 01:47:42.934
If they're following you,
we are stuck.

01:47:43.954 --> 01:47:46.814
- Do you have the driver?
- Yeah, he's outside.

01:47:47.474 --> 01:47:50.120
Okay. Tell Christopher
to meet us at my club.

01:47:50.162 --> 01:47:52.160
At least, we'll have
some peace and quiet.

01:47:52.524 --> 01:47:54.269
- He's here.
- Chris!

01:47:54.562 --> 01:47:55.911
Hey, hey.

01:47:56.085 --> 01:47:57.551
Are you all right?

01:47:57.984 --> 01:48:00.344
- Did you get my messages?
- Um...

01:48:00.914 --> 01:48:04.024
Klaus thinks that the paparazzi
are following you from the hospital.

01:48:04.709 --> 01:48:07.416
I don't know.
I didn't see any.

01:48:07.722 --> 01:48:10.296
They can get a picture of us tonight,
it'll be a total disaster.

01:48:10.336 --> 01:48:11.924
I mean, it'll spread like wildfire.

01:48:12.018 --> 01:48:13.602
I'm gonna call my driver.

01:48:15.767 --> 01:48:17.619
Hey Emily,
come pick us up.

01:48:18.046 --> 01:48:19.833
- All right.
- Here...

01:48:20.618 --> 01:48:22.386
The address of my club.

01:48:22.607 --> 01:48:26.176
We go first, wait 5 minutes,
take a taxi and join us.

01:48:52.410 --> 01:48:54.777
Oh, fuck!
They're following us.

01:48:56.949 --> 01:48:58.239
Hey, Ari?

01:48:58.592 --> 01:49:00.965
No, there's, there's
no news here from the hospital.

01:49:01.122 --> 01:49:03.465
Yeah, I could really
use you right now.

01:49:04.480 --> 01:49:06.365
Whatever the first plane out is.

01:49:06.451 --> 01:49:09.345
I'm stuck here in London
till the end of the year.

01:49:09.411 --> 01:49:11.098
Rehearsals start tomorrow.

01:49:11.372 --> 01:49:12.966
If she doesn't make it,...

01:49:13.606 --> 01:49:16.552
it's gonna be a nuclear fucking winter.

01:49:17.175 --> 01:49:19.235
What do you want to do?
Change hotels?

01:49:19.382 --> 01:49:20.389
No way.

01:49:20.442 --> 01:49:23.048
Wherever I go, they're just
gonna find me and chase me down.

01:49:23.459 --> 01:49:25.230
I'll rather stay where I am.

01:49:25.463 --> 01:49:26.763
You know, it's...

01:49:26.907 --> 01:49:28.083
I'm fine with it.

01:49:28.203 --> 01:49:29.830
It must be hard for Chris.

01:49:29.902 --> 01:49:31.837
The media is going to crucify him.

01:49:31.888 --> 01:49:33.777
No, no.
I'll take the heat.

01:49:33.989 --> 01:49:35.797
I'll be the home wrecker.

01:49:36.352 --> 01:49:38.125
I'm used to the nasty shit
written about me.

01:49:38.166 --> 01:49:39.326
I can obviously care less.

01:49:39.395 --> 01:49:41.500
Do you want us to cancel
tomorrow's rehearsal?

01:49:41.661 --> 01:49:43.227
Maria, would you mind?

01:49:43.285 --> 01:49:44.747
Mmm, of course not.

01:49:44.790 --> 01:49:45.804
No way.

01:49:45.851 --> 01:49:47.084
- Mmm.
- No, I don't.

01:49:47.167 --> 01:49:48.577
I'd rather work.

01:49:53.428 --> 01:49:55.108
We didn't get to talk much?

01:49:55.266 --> 01:49:56.311
No

01:49:56.767 --> 01:49:59.328
I'll have the new scenes
dropped off at the front desk.

01:49:59.368 --> 01:50:01.723
And we'll talk about them seriously.

01:50:01.790 --> 01:50:04.670
Yeah, we can do that tomorrow.
After rehearsal.

01:50:05.640 --> 01:50:08.676
I'm drained after a work day.
It's not the best time for me.

01:50:08.715 --> 01:50:10.916
I know.
It's the same for me.

01:50:11.145 --> 01:50:15.198
And next weekend, I have to see
my kids in southern Italy.

01:50:16.665 --> 01:50:17.916
We'll manage.

01:50:17.979 --> 01:50:19.239
Okay, good night.

01:50:19.325 --> 01:50:20.612
Good night.

01:50:30.823 --> 01:50:33.557
When I tell you about you,
how much I appreciate you,

01:50:33.610 --> 01:50:35.337
it's to remind me,

01:50:35.406 --> 01:50:39.066
how happy they are to grant you
what they never granted me.

01:50:39.972 --> 01:50:41.448
They're using you...

01:50:54.010 --> 01:50:55.010
Hi.

01:50:55.043 --> 01:50:56.716
I printed everything out.

01:50:56.756 --> 01:50:59.749
If you want an English solicitor
to take a look at the papers, tell me.

01:50:59.889 --> 01:51:02.889
I know a bilingual girl
who specializes in Paris real estate.

01:51:05.501 --> 01:51:06.862
That's the sales agreement.

01:51:06.903 --> 01:51:10.161
Your ex-husband is buying your half of
the apartment for the price you agreed to.

01:51:10.215 --> 01:51:12.261
Oh, no, I don't want to discuss it

01:51:12.443 --> 01:51:14.116
Maybe, I was wrong.

01:51:14.362 --> 01:51:17.282
And that's the sales agreement
for the Studio on the Rue du Chemin Vert.

01:51:17.349 --> 01:51:19.841
Yeah, it's expensive,
but it's worth it.

01:51:20.561 --> 01:51:23.036
- You say he's ready to sign?
- Tomorrow, as planned.

01:51:23.270 --> 01:51:25.217
You take the Eurostar at 8:15,

01:51:25.443 --> 01:51:28.370
leave Paris at 5:00, and you'll be
back in London in time for dinner.

01:51:28.493 --> 01:51:30.300
- Okay.
- If you want, I can travel with you.

01:51:30.346 --> 01:51:31.893
No, I'm fine.

01:51:36.731 --> 01:51:39.057
What do I tell Piers Roaldson?

01:51:39.277 --> 01:51:40.891
Remind me who he is.

01:51:41.020 --> 01:51:44.604
He's shooting a film at Sains
called "Electric Shockwave".

01:51:45.640 --> 01:51:46.980
What has he done?

01:51:47.240 --> 01:51:48.860
Nothing.
He's twenty-five.

01:51:49.146 --> 01:51:52.003
But, Jay says he's good and
that has been "green lit".

01:51:52.692 --> 01:51:53.905
What's the part?

01:51:54.043 --> 01:51:55.892
They haven't sent it over yet.

01:51:56.376 --> 01:51:57.738
It's the lead?

01:51:57.817 --> 01:52:01.427
I think your character will be
some sort of hybrid.

01:52:02.528 --> 01:52:05.533
Mmm, a creation of modern genetics,
but with a soul.

01:52:06.034 --> 01:52:08.687
It's set in the near future,
the 23rd century.

01:52:09.249 --> 01:52:10.507
On Earth?

01:52:11.303 --> 01:52:13.543
Maybe, I'm not sure.

01:52:15.446 --> 01:52:16.779
Hi.

01:52:17.314 --> 01:52:19.270
- Where?
- Over there.

01:52:19.737 --> 01:52:21.177
Thank you.

01:52:21.477 --> 01:52:23.385
Um, tell Piers,
I'm interested, and uh...

01:52:23.479 --> 01:52:25.553
I'll read the script
next week, okay?

01:52:25.720 --> 01:52:28.515
And uh...there are
the new scenes Klaus sent you?

01:52:28.555 --> 01:52:29.939
Oh, yes, I forgot.

01:52:30.122 --> 01:52:31.629
Want to try the lines?

01:52:32.272 --> 01:52:34.785
No, I haven't read the pages yet.

01:52:35.311 --> 01:52:36.678
He wants to know what you think.

01:52:36.779 --> 01:52:38.490
Why doesn't he just call me?

01:52:38.883 --> 01:52:40.876
Maybe, he's waiting
for your reaction.

01:52:41.322 --> 01:52:43.189
You've had the scenes
for two weeks.

01:52:43.422 --> 01:52:44.816
Yeah, I understand.

01:52:45.506 --> 01:52:49.306
But, I'd rather discover them at the last
minute and not over-think it. It's...

01:52:49.406 --> 01:52:51.752
it's the only way
I can keep it spontaneous.

01:52:52.471 --> 01:52:55.411
It's how I um...
prepared Sigrid 20 years ago.

01:52:55.464 --> 01:52:57.686
I'll do the same thing
with Helena.

01:52:58.644 --> 01:53:01.951
If he asks you, just tell him
I think they're very good.

01:54:01.212 --> 01:54:03.818
Very good.
But, it's still a little long.

01:54:04.422 --> 01:54:06.945
- Jo-Ann, can you hear me?
- Uh, yeah.

01:54:07.135 --> 01:54:09.331
Do the same thing,
but speed it up a little.

01:54:09.391 --> 01:54:10.285
Okay.

01:54:10.311 --> 01:54:12.008
Why don't you just
forget one of the files?

01:54:12.041 --> 01:54:13.340
There are plenty.

01:54:13.417 --> 01:54:15.495
- We do it one more time.
- Okay.

01:54:18.939 --> 01:54:20.305
Excuse me.

01:54:20.888 --> 01:54:22.842
Tomorrow is our final dress rehearsal.

01:54:22.883 --> 01:54:25.482
- I know, thanks for taking the time.
- My pleasure.

01:54:25.944 --> 01:54:27.782
I'll just switch this on.

01:54:28.602 --> 01:54:31.175
Uh, may I have
a cup of coffee, please.

01:54:31.548 --> 01:54:33.711
Well, you can imagine
my first question.

01:54:33.797 --> 01:54:38.178
Will the media frenzy around
Jo-Ann Ellis steal the spotlight.

01:54:38.948 --> 01:54:41.961
All that matters is the show,
the rest is of no importance.

01:54:42.025 --> 01:54:45.087
And fortunately,
Dorothea pulled through.

01:54:45.329 --> 01:54:47.365
I know you have a new take on it,
but...

01:54:47.475 --> 01:54:50.772
will the audience be receptive?
Or might they be too distracted?

01:54:50.825 --> 01:54:52.619
I, I suppose that's my question.

01:54:52.769 --> 01:54:54.736
I hope they'll be receptive.

01:54:54.946 --> 01:54:59.906
So, so you think the shows are air-tight,
no connection to the outside world?

01:55:00.035 --> 01:55:01.145
No

01:55:01.398 --> 01:55:04.392
No, each theatre goer
brings his own subjectivity.

01:55:04.507 --> 01:55:07.792
And it's generally
not defined by tabloid headlines.

01:55:08.234 --> 01:55:10.150
Some will go for the smell of scandal.

01:55:10.196 --> 01:55:14.137
So will they see the show you had in mind,
or something else?

01:55:16.108 --> 01:55:17.155
Jo-Ann!

01:55:17.239 --> 01:55:18.292
What's up?

01:55:18.340 --> 01:55:20.036
I wanted to ask you.

01:55:20.180 --> 01:55:22.923
You know the scene
at the beginning act three,

01:55:22.952 --> 01:55:25.136
when you tell me you wanna leave,
and...

01:55:25.276 --> 01:55:27.075
I get on my knees
and I beg you to stay?

01:55:27.135 --> 01:55:29.118
You're on the phone
ordering pepperoncini pizza

01:55:29.151 --> 01:55:30.965
- Uh-huh.
- for your co-workers in accounting.

01:55:31.018 --> 01:55:34.080
Well, you...
you leave without looking at me.

01:55:34.503 --> 01:55:36.933
As if I didn't exist.

01:55:37.193 --> 01:55:38.447
Um...

01:55:39.236 --> 01:55:41.123
If you could pause for a second,

01:55:41.276 --> 01:55:43.346
you know,
Helena's distress would last longer

01:55:43.399 --> 01:55:46.266
when she's left alone in her office.

01:55:47.556 --> 01:55:50.543
Well, the way you're playing it,
um...

01:55:50.679 --> 01:55:54.496
the audience follows you out,
but instantly forgets about her, so...

01:55:54.623 --> 01:55:56.139
So...

01:55:56.606 --> 01:55:58.066
So what?

01:55:58.513 --> 01:56:00.796
Well, when I played Sigrid,
I...

01:56:00.866 --> 01:56:03.176
I held it longer.
I thought it was...

01:56:03.495 --> 01:56:06.803
more powerful.
I mean, it really played well.

01:56:07.075 --> 01:56:10.781
Well, no-one really gives a fuck
about Helena at that point, do they?

01:56:11.121 --> 01:56:12.975
I'm sorry. But, I mean,
it's pretty clear to me

01:56:13.008 --> 01:56:14.828
this poor woman's all washed up.

01:56:15.102 --> 01:56:17.345
I mean your character, right?
Not you.

01:56:17.399 --> 01:56:18.572
And...

01:56:18.680 --> 01:56:21.245
When Sigrid leaves Helena's office,

01:56:21.370 --> 01:56:22.818
Helena's a wreck.

01:56:22.903 --> 01:56:25.406
And we get it.
You know, it time to move on.

01:56:25.593 --> 01:56:28.573
I think they want
what comes next.

01:56:28.974 --> 01:56:32.173
If you just held it,
a few seconds longer.

01:56:32.473 --> 01:56:35.033
It doesn't quite feel right for me,
Maria.

01:56:37.486 --> 01:56:38.995
You're right.

01:56:40.147 --> 01:56:41.661
Yeah.

01:56:42.346 --> 01:56:43.763
I, I um...

01:56:45.044 --> 01:56:48.550
I think I'm, I'm lost in my memories.

01:56:48.690 --> 01:56:51.110
You, you think you've
forgotten your old habits,

01:56:51.154 --> 01:56:53.613
but, they all...
they all come back.

01:56:53.731 --> 01:56:55.206
I have to break them.

01:56:55.540 --> 01:56:57.526
I guess you do.

01:57:22.741 --> 01:57:25.216
- Hi, come in.
- Hi.

01:57:25.823 --> 01:57:28.841
Thanks so much for seeing me tonight.
I really appreciate it.

01:57:29.048 --> 01:57:32.355
We're leaving early tomorrow morning
for a location scout in the Ukraine.

01:57:32.898 --> 01:57:35.392
That's where we're going to be
shooting our exteriors, mostly.

01:57:35.452 --> 01:57:37.332
So, I, I read your script.

01:57:37.666 --> 01:57:39.004
Yeah, well, um...

01:57:39.121 --> 01:57:42.500
I know we've never met, but,
I actually wrote it with you in mind.

01:57:42.906 --> 01:57:44.300
As a mutant?

01:57:44.657 --> 01:57:48.413
I'm trying to consider genetics
from a more human point of view.

01:57:49.607 --> 01:57:52.014
When I was reading it,
um...

01:57:52.425 --> 01:57:54.127
I imagined someone much younger.

01:57:54.202 --> 01:57:55.615
Maybe, me younger, actually.

01:57:55.668 --> 01:57:59.542
But, you were seeing me in movies
that were made years ago, I...

01:57:59.928 --> 01:58:01.095
I've changed.

01:58:01.147 --> 01:58:02.628
She has no age.

01:58:03.262 --> 01:58:05.711
Or else...
she's every age at once.

01:58:05.776 --> 01:58:07.196
Like all of us.

01:58:08.328 --> 01:58:10.041
Can I be frank?

01:58:11.737 --> 01:58:14.263
Maybe, because I'm
working with her, but...

01:58:14.550 --> 01:58:18.303
as I was reading it,
I... I kept thinking about Jo-Ann.

01:58:18.575 --> 01:58:20.098
Yeah, well...

01:58:20.293 --> 01:58:24.105
personally, I never think
about Jo-Ann Ellis.

01:58:24.479 --> 01:58:26.250
You're wrong.
She's smart.

01:58:26.390 --> 01:58:27.720
And talented.

01:58:27.909 --> 01:58:29.190
She is modern.

01:58:29.251 --> 01:58:30.423
Just like your character.

01:58:30.476 --> 01:58:32.130
My character isn't modern.

01:58:32.242 --> 01:58:33.855
Notin in that way, anyway

01:58:33.942 --> 01:58:35.049
She's...

01:58:35.335 --> 01:58:36.769
outside of time.

01:58:36.878 --> 01:58:38.616
"Outside of time."

01:58:41.631 --> 01:58:44.596
I don't understand,
it's too abstract for me

01:58:44.723 --> 01:58:46.130
Sorry.

01:58:46.295 --> 01:58:48.923
I uh...
I don't like this era.

01:58:49.302 --> 01:58:50.855
You're wrong.
It's yours.

01:58:50.911 --> 01:58:53.155
Amen!
I didn't choose it.

01:58:53.618 --> 01:58:57.258
And if my era is Jo-Ann Ellis
and viral internet scandals,

01:58:57.328 --> 01:59:00.121
I think I'm entitled
to feel unrelated, aren't I?

01:59:01.368 --> 01:59:02.948
I mean, it's nothing against her.

01:59:02.996 --> 01:59:05.558
I guess I just assumed
you'd understand.

01:59:08.001 --> 01:59:09.608
Curtain in five minutes.

01:59:09.741 --> 01:59:12.228
- How's the house?
- Full.

